Commentary: Good ball to start. A fuller one around off, Agarwal looks to block but the ball takes the outer half of the bat and goes towards point.
Bowls this one on middle and a good length. Agarwal this time is solid in his block.

FOUR! Off the mark in style! Room on offer outside off, Agarwal latches onto it and drives it through cover-point to earn the first boundary of the innings. That didn't come out of the middle but Agarwal won't mind.
Good length ball around off, Agarwal defends it out.
A muted appeal! Slightly fuller ball which came back into Agarwal. He looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads. No chance of  the LBW anyway as this was pitched outside off.
Good length ball, blocked by Agarwal solidly off the back foot.
He starts with a sixth stump line ball which further seams away from the batter. Rohit leaves it alone.

FOUR! Top shot to get off the mark. Rabada dishes this slightly shortish length ball but on the fifth stump line. Rohit accepts the room outside off and slams it powerfully over point and into the fence.
In the channel outside off this time on a good length, Rohit does not fiddle with it.
Slightly shortish length outside off, Rohit makes another leave.
Another ball which is very wide from the off stump, Rohit lets it go to the keeper. The ball moved further away after pitching.
Another leave from Rohit. This one is pitched outside off again.
One more ball which is wide outside off, it is left alone.
Well bowled! This is angled into the batter now, it pitches around off and then nips back in just a touch. Agarwal looks to defend but it goes off the inner half through mid-wicket for one.

BEATEN! Lovely delivery! The South African bowlers are getting the ball to talk here. Not a lot Rohit could have done there. It lands on off and it is on a length. Rohit looks to defend the original trajectory but the ball shapes away after pitching. Whizzes past the outside edge.
This one is outside off, a harmless delivery. Left alone.
Rohit takes a few steps down the track, maybe to negotiate the movement. Philander hence, shortens the length which means the ball has lesser time to do its bit. Rohit blocks it out easily.
A tentative poke to end! A good over this by Philander. This starts outside off and then moves away further. Rohit hangs his bat out and the ball once again goes past the outside edge.
Goes wide of the crease and angles this one into the off pole. Agarwal goes back and defends it onto the ground.
Another one wide outside off, it is left alone. Not a good start by Rabada, he has been too wide.
One more wasteful delivery! Short and outside off, it is left alone.
Better! This is initially angled into the off pole but then leaves the batter. Agarwal is drawn into playing at it but the ball beats the outside edge by a long way though.
This whizzes closes past the outside edge. However, this is another needless shot, could have left this delivery. It is a little wide outside off. Agarwal looks to defend but gets beaten.
A good bumper to end! It is on off, Agarwal hops and keeps it down towards cover.
Slightly fuller and on off, Rohit looks to stroke it through the off side but it goes off the inner half towards mid off.
Fuller again but not quite there for the drive, it is bowled outside off. Left alone.

Almost! This is top, top stuff from Philander. Very unlucky there he did not get Rohit. He took the last two away, this time, he lands it around off and then gets it to jag back in. Rohit maybe expected it to go away again and lets it be. To his luck though, the ball bounces and goes over the middle pole.
Good delivery again! This lands on off and then jags back in. Rohit looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Now the outswinger but it is outside off, left alone. Once again Rohit is seen taking a few steps down the track.
Now this one nips back in from outside off. Does not come in enough though to make the batter play. Another good over from Philander comes to an end.
Slightly shorter and outside off, Agarwal pushes it away from the body through cover-point for two.
Shortish again on off, blocked.

EDGY FOUR! Luck now favoring India. This lands on middle and then straightens. Agarwal looks to work it on the leg side but due to the movement, it goes off the leading edge, between gully and second slip and down to the third man fence.
Good length and on off, Agarwal plays it with a straight bat and into the ground.
Beauty! This is on a length and it straightens once again. Agarwal is squared up as he tries to put bat on ball. Fails to do so as the ball beats the outside edge.
Angles this one into the batter, Agarwal gets right behind the line and blocks it out.
Good length and on off, it is defended onto the ground.
Keeps on landing it on a length. Rohit though is solid in defense this time.
FOUR! Slashes and gets the result he wanted! Slightly short and outside off, Rohit transfers his weight onto the back foot and slashes at it, it goes past the fielder at gully and into the fence.
VP goes back to attacking the off pole, Sharma defends it out.
Just outside off again and on a length. Rohit ends up playing outside the line, he gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Extra bounce there! Well played in the end. It is another length ball, takes off after pitching. Rohit does well to take one hand off the handle and push it to mid off.
Shorter and on the body, Agarwal works it with the angle to mid-wicket.
On the shorter side on middle, it is kept out.
This is angled into the batter, it is worked to mid-wicket.
One more delivery on a length, this one is pushed to covers.
An appeal but it is too high! This is on a length and it jags back in. Agarwal looks to defend but is hit high on the pads. An appeal but it is turned down.
Outside off, it is left alone.
Tosses it up on middle, Rohit drives it to mid off.
Off the inner half! The arm ball, it drifts back in from outside off. Rohit looks to defend but does so outside the line, it goes off the inner half down towards fine leg for two.
Very full and on middle, Sharma eases it down to long on for one.
On the stumps once again but no turn yet visible for Maharaj. Agarwal defends it out.
On middle and flatter, Agarwal is solid in defense.
Slower through the air this time, it lands on middle and goes on with the arm. Agarwal lunges and keeps it out.
On the shorter side and on off, Rohit goes back and keeps it out.
Back of a length again and on off, Rohit plays it to mid off.
OHHH! This is slightly fuller, it comes back in and also skids through. Rohit is a touch late to get his bat down, it hits the inner half and then goes onto hit the pads.
A good bumper on middle, Rohit initially looks to pull but then bails out.
On off, Rohit once again manages to keep it out.
On off, this is kept out.
Tosses it up on middle, Agarwal plays it to short extra cover.
Flighted ball on off, Agarwal keeps it out.

Hint of turn there! Causes problems straightaway. This is slower through the air, it lands on off and then turns away a little. Agarwal is rooted to his crease, in the end, he looks to poke at it. Gets beaten.
This one goes on with the arm and it lands on middle, Agarwal keeps it out.
This is flatter and quicker on off, Agarwal gets his bat down in time and keeps it out.
One more flighted ball on off, Agarwal is solid in defense. So not a lot of turn for Maharaj as of now. He has kept it tight.
Outside off, it is left alone.
Lovely shot for two! Shorter in length, Rohit has no problems as he goes back and pulls it towards deep square leg. A fielder in the deep runs to his left and stops it, not cleanly but saves two.
Goes wide of the crease and angles it into the off pole. Blocked.

Another couple! Fuller in length and on off, Rohit shows the full face of the bat and strokes it towards the bowler. Rabada gets a hand to it, the ball rolls towards long off. Mid on gives it a chase and keeps it down to two.
On middle, Rohit works it to short mid-wicket.
Outside off, Sharma does not fiddle with it.
Gives it air and lands it on middle, MA pushes it to covers.
This is worked with the angle to the man at mid-wicket.
This is floated outside off, Agarwal drives it but the ball hits the fielder at silly point and then goes towards cover-point.
On off, Agarwal lunges and keeps it out.
FOUR! Good shot that, it is juts a push by Agarwal. It was timed brilliantly. This is a touch too full from Maharaj. Agarwal punches it past the diving mid on fielder and it races away to the fence.
Drags his length back this time and it is kept out.
This is on a length and outside off, Rohit opens the face of the bat, guides it through point for one.
Outside off, left alone.
On off this time, it is kept out.
FOUR! Exquisite timing once again. Another bowler pays the price for going too full. It is outside off too. Agarwal leans into it and creams it through covers.
Drags his length back and also gets his line right, this is on off. Defended.
On a length and around off, this is guided to gully.
Flighted ball on off, Rohit guides it towards cover and gets to the other end.
Flatter and on off, Agarwal plays it late and towards backward point.
Once again plays this ball late, it is hit towards backward point. Away from the fielder this time so a single is taken.
Floats it up on off, Rohit pushes it towards covers.
Loopy delivery and on off, Rohit prods forward and keeps it out.
Rohit misses out there! This is short and outside off, Rohit cuts but finds the man at point.
Philander continues after drinks, shortish ball outside off, poked to point.
On a good length, outside off, left alone.
Back of a length delivery, worked to deep point for one.
Defends this close to the body.
On the pads worked to the leg side for a single.
Knocks the ball outside off to the covers for one.
Tosses it up on middle, this is defended onto the ground.
Flatter and on the pads, this is worked to short leg.
Slower through the air outside off, Agarwal plays it out again.
Flatter and quicker outside off, it is kept out.
FOUR! Width on offer and Agarwal takes toll of it. This is outside off and it is slower outside off. Agarwal goes after it, hits it through cover-point and the ball races away to the fence.
Goes back to attacking the stumps, Agarwal manages to keep it out again.
Fullish outside off, Sharma caresses it to deep point for single.
Gets his head on top of the ball to defend it.
Camps on the back foot to work the ball to the off side.
Agarwal stays on the back foot again and works it to deep point for a single.
Fullish ball around off played to mid off.
Good length ball on middle and off, Sharma fends it of the inner half of the bat to mid on.
Tossed  up on off, Agarwal fends it to mid on.
Floats it up on middle, this is hit to the fielder at mid on.
Tosses this one up on off, Agarwal strokes it to mid off.
Defended off the back foot by the batsman.
A little too straight, this is worked to the fielder at short leg.
A maiden to begin with Piedt. This is on off, Agarwal keeps it out.

SIX! First biggie of the morning. 50 up for India. It is also the first 50-run stand for the opening wicket after nine innings for India. Rohit comes down the track and launches it over cow corner for a maximum.
Hit a six and get off strike. Played Sharma. Worked to mid off for a single.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Outside off played to covers.
Agarwal plays that off the front foot and into the ground.
Tossed up delivery on middle and watchfully defended.
Fuller outside off, this is played wide of cover for a single.
A low full toss, Agarwal hits it down to long on and a single is taken.
Floated up outside off, Rohit defends it out.
Tosses it up outside off, it goes on with the arm. Rohit defends inside the line, it goes off the outside edge towards third man for one.
Shorter and outside off, this one stays a touch low. Agarwal pushes it to covers.

FOUR! DEFT! Picked his spot nicely. The bowler is bowling without a point so Agarwal hits this one through that region. It is flatter and outside off, Agarwal waits for it and plays it very late and bags a boundary. Runs coming thick and fast for India now. 14 from the last two.
Tossed up on middle, played with the spin to mid off.
Angled in on leg, played to mid on for a single.
Shortish outside off, cut to the covers.
Defended off the front foot to short cover.
Looks to cut the ball. Misses. De Kock holds the ball.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Angled on to the pads, defended to the leg side.
Flicked off the pads for a for a single to the onside.
SIX! Tossed up on off, Agarwal gets to the pitch of the ball and launches it back over the bowler's head for a maximum.
Comes round the wicket and bowls it on the pads, it is worked to mid-wicket.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Gets in the line of the ball and defends.
Tosses it up on off, Rohit strokes it to covers.
FOUR! Short ball and put away! Also, there is width on offer, not a lot but enough for Rohit to go back and slap it through point for a boundary. Raining boundaries at the moment.
Flatter and on off, defended.
Loopy ball on middle, this is hit back towards the bowler who fumbles but the ball hits the non-striker and no runs is conceded.
On the stumps, Rohit lunges and keeps it out.
Shorter and outside off, Rohit goes back and pushes it through covers. There is a fielder in the deep so just one.
Tossed up outside the leg stump line. Sharma lunges to sweep but misses. Piedt appeals in vain.
Tossed up on leg. Blocked  to short leg.
SIX! Another one. Comes to the pitch of the ball and launches it for a maximum over long on.
Gets in the line of the ball and works it to mid-wicket.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
This is fuller and on the pads, it is worked to mid-wicket.
This is angled into the batter, defended.
Goes wide of the crease and bowls it on middle, Agarwal is once again solid in defense.
Back of a length on off, Agarwal pushes it to covers.
One more delivery angled into the batter, Agarwal stays back and keeps it out.
A maiden! Another length ball and on off, Agarwal keeps it out.
Starts off with a very full ball on middle, Rohit jams it out.
Rohit comes down the track but does not get to the pitch of the ball. Ends up pushing it to mid on.
Lands this on middle, Rohit prods forward and keeps it out.

FOUR! Lovely use of the wrists there by Rohit. He skips down the track again and gets to the pitch of it this time. Does not go hard and just whips it through mid-wicket. The ball races away to the fence. Rohit is into his own now.
A single now as this is pushed through covers for one. A boundary away from a 50 now.
A dot to end! Flatter and on off, it is kept out.
Rohit uncomfortably gets a leading edge to a shortish delivery outside off to point, where the fielder dives and saves a run.
Angled in on middle, Sharma blocks it out.
Comes in with the angle again, Sharma defends it as well.
Angled further on the pads, Rohit flicks it to mid-wicket for a couple of runs.
Camps on the back foot and blocks the ball.
Full toss on leg, played to mid on.
A freebie! A full toss but all Agarwal could do is, hit it down to long on for one.
Flatter and on off, Rohit defends it.
Gives it a lot of air and lands it on off, Rohit drives it to covers.
Well bowled! Sees Rohit come down the track so shortens his length. Rohit does well to adjust and keep it out. He played it well though as there was extra bounce there. Played it with soft hands.
The batsman works it down the leg side.

In the air... just wide! FOUR! Fifty up for Rohit. He brings it up in a streaky manner but he won't care. Excellent start for him as a Test opener. 11th in this format. It has been a very entertaining knock from him so far. Got through the initial tough phase and now looks extremely good out there. He has a chance to make it big here. He brings out the sweep shot but due to the extra bounce, it catches the top edge. Goes uppishly but wide of Rabada at backward square leg who puts in a dive. The ball then races to the fence.
Back of a length ball angled in, Agarwal defends.
Length ball outside off, Agarwal camps on the back foot to block it.
Drops it short outside off, Agarwal shoulders arms to let it through.
Short again, angled on middle this time. Agarwal gets out of the line of the ball.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Covers the line of the ball and defends. LUNCH ON DAY 1.
Starts off with a flatter delivery on off, Rohit defends it out.

FOUR! Rohit continues from where he left off before the break! First runs in this session is in the form of a boundary. Slightly short and outside off, Rohit goes back and punches it through covers, it is in the gap and it races away.
Attacks the stumps now and it is slightly fuller. Kept out.
Very full this time, Rohit eases it down to long on for one.
On the off pole, Agarwal keeps it out.
On the pads, Agarwal looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads.
Good length outside off, Sharma plays it with soft hands to the off side.
Comes on the front foot and defends.
Full ball on middle, Sharma flicks off the front foot to mid-wicket for a single.
Bangs it in short outside, it doesn't rise much. Agarwal cuts it to deep point for a couple.
Persists with the short pitch line outside off, in an attempt to guide it to third man, Agarwal plays it into the pitch.
Fuller and on on middle, Agarwal blocks it out.
Tosses it up on off, Rohit lunges and keeps it out.
Well fielded! Rohit comes down the track and works it to the right of the bowler. He dives and pushes it towards short mid-wicket, saves a run.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
On middle, this is also defended.
Another one on middle, Rohit easily keeps it out.
Rohit comes down the track again but does not get to the pitch of the ball. He defends it in the end. A maiden by Maharaj.
Fullish ball on off, Agarwal defends it off the front foot.
A little shorter this time, outside off, Agarwal flat bats it to point.
Full ball on the pads, squirted to square leg. No run.
Short outside off now, Agarwal cuts it and Markram at backward point makes a diving stop.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Good length around off, Agarwal blocks it again. Another maiden over.
Floated outside off, Sharma blocks it back.
Extra bounce on this occasion, Sharma looks to defend but is hit on the glove.
Sharma  defends it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Gets within the line of the ball and blocks.
Angled in to the batsman, Sharma blocks it yet again.
Almost a replica of the previous delivery. Same result, Sharma blocks it.
Full outside off, Agarwal pushes it to the covers.
On Middle and off, Agarwal gets an inside edge onto his pads.

FOUR! 1st 100-run stand for the opening wicket for India after 24 innings. Full on the pads, Agarwal powers it with his wrists to the mid-wicket boundary. The mid on fielder gave it a chase but it was in vain. First runs after 22 balls.
Good length outside off, worked to backward point by Agarwal.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Outside off, defended to the covers.
Flatter and on off, it is kept out.
On middle, defended.
Sharma comes down the track but it is a short ball. He pushes it down to long on for one.

SIX! That is some way to get to a half ton. What a shot. Wow! Probably the shot of the game so far. It is Agarwal's 4th fifty in this format. Maharaj floats this up outside off, Agarwal goes  inside out, lofts it with utmost ease over covers and it carries all the way. A big one is on the offer for him too.
On middle, it is kept out.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Leg bye. LBW Appeal! But it's not to be. Angled in, it hits him on the pads, but the ball is going down leg and the umpire ignores it. The Proteas too do not go for a review. They sneak in a leg bye.
Good length ball on off, Agarwal plays it to the off side for a single.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
FOUR! Back of a length outside off, Sharma camps on the back foot and steers it past the diving gully fielder for a boundary.
Shortish in length around off, it's defended off the back foot
Blocks yet again. Sharma and Agarwal are taking calculated risks.
Shorter and on middle, this is pushed down to long on for one.
Loopy ball on off, Rohit prods forward and keeps it out.
One more tossed up ball on off, Rohit is solid in defense.
Well bowled but well played too! Rohit comes down the track, Maharaj shortens his length and bowls it outside off. Rohit adjusts and slaps it through covers for one.
On middle, it is kept out.
The last ball also is defended as it is bowled on the stumps.
FOUR! Back of a length and outside off, Sharma goes on his toes and punches it through the covers for a boundary
On middle and leg, worked to the on side.
Short and on middle, Sharma pulls it to square leg for a single. Piedt does a neat job in the field to keep it down to a single.
Outside off played to point.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Good length on middle and off, Agarwal defends it.
Slower through the air around off, Rohit comes down the track to block.
Slightly shortish ball outside off, Rohit goes back to punch towards deep cover for a single.
Fuller one on middle, Agarwal blocks it out.
Around off this time, pushed towards point.
Loopy ball outside off, Agarwal drives it through mid off for a single.
Fuller around off, Rohit lunges to block it out.
Full ball on off, Agarwal defends it off the front foot.
In the corridor of uncertainty, Agarwal shoulders arms to it.
On the pads, worked through backward square leg for a single.
Good length ball around off, Sharma pushes it for a single to the covers.
Good bumper, Agarwal ducks under it to let it pass.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
A flighted ball around off, Rohit lunges to block it towards point.
Shortish ball outside off, Rohit goes back and punches it towards deep point for a single.
Flatter one around off, Agarwal taps it towards cover.
A fuller one around off this time, Agarwal is solid in his block as he pushes it towards cover.
Around off on a fullish length this time, Agarwal keeps it out with ease.
Fullish ball around off, Agarwal defends it out.
FOUR! Wide outside off and short, Sharma rocks back and powerfully slaps the ball to the mid-wicket boundary.
Good length ball outside off, Sharma pushes it towards point. Agarwal wanted a single but Rohit is not interested. There is a direct hit at the non-striker's end but Agarwal is home safely.
Back of a length ball around middle and leg, Rohit pulls it behind square leg for a single.
Short of length outside off, Agarwal guides it towards point for a single.
Full on middle, Rohit whips it off the pads but finds the short mid-wicket fielder.
On the pads this time, Rohit guides it off the pads towards mid-wicket for a single.
Floated on middle and defended off the front foot.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Glides it on the pads, Sharma, works it back past the the bowler for a single.
Stays on the back foot and defends the ball.
Shortish and wide outside off, Agarwal cuts it to deep point for a single.
Rohit comes down the track but does not get to the pitch of it. He pushes it uppishly but short of short covers who stops it with a dive to his right.
Flighted outside off, played off the front foot to mid off.
Charges down the track, to the pitch of the ball and squirts it through the covers for a single.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Played through mid-wicket for a single.
Defends the ball off the back foot.
Flighted outside off, the ball spins in sharply to the right handed Agarwal, who uses his wrists to work the ball to the onside.
Shorter and outside off, Rohit cuts it through point and a single is taken.
Fuller this time, Agarwal strokes it to covers.
On the off pole, Agarwal lunges forward and defends it onto the ground.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Loopy ball on off, Bavuma strokes it towards cover where Bavuma makes a half stop but can't stop a run.
The arm ball on the off pole, it is defended.
FOUR! Hammered! That went to the fence like a tracer bullet. Agarwal comes down the track and smashes it past the non-striker. No chance for anyone there as it races to the fence.
Works it with the turn now towards mid-wicket.
On middle, this is kept out.
FOUR! A hit-me ball and Agarwal takes full toll of it. A half-tracker on middle, Agarwal goes back and pulls it behind square on the leg side. Second boundary in the over.
Gives it a nice amount of air and lands it on off, Mayank eases it down to long on for one. 150 up for India.
On the off pole, Rohit defends it out.
On middle, Agarwal lunges forward and defends it onto the ground.
NO BALL!  It is on middle, Agarwal keeps it out. The No ball was due to the silly point fielder encroaching the pitch.
Another ball on middle, MA lunges and keeps it out.
Floats it up outside off, Agarwal strokes it to covers.
Lands it on middle, Mayank prods forward and keeps it out.
Another defensive stroke to this delivery on off.
A dot to end! This is flatter and outside off, it is guided to point. Another over goes by and the Indians manage to play it at ease.
Floats it outside off, Sharma defends it off the front foot.
Comes on down the track only to block the ball.
Full and flight on middle and off, Sharma blocks it off the front foot to mid on. Bavuma stationed there, dives and makes a stop.
SIX! Charges down the track and gets to the pitch of the ball to smack it over the mid-wicket boundary for a maximum.
SIX! one after the other. This time it's over the long on boundary, Gets to the pitch of the ball and launches it. This one went further.
On the pads clipped to the on side.
A little turn there! The length though is shorter so the batter has enough time to go back, adjust and guide it to point.
Floats it up on off, this is kept out.
On middle, it takes off after pitching. Agarwal plays it down onto the ground nicely.
On the pads, it is worked towards square leg.
Another forward defensive stroke to a ball on middle.
A single to end as Agarwal eases it down to long off.
FOUR! First ball and he clears fielders in the covers for a boundary. Superb placement.
Flicked to the on side. No run.
On the pads, Agarwal turns it to the leg side.
Loopy ball around off, Agarwal comes forward to block but the ball takes an inside edge and goes past the stumps towards the leg side for a single.
Rohit played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Floats it up on off, this is driven through covers for a single.
FOUR! Deft! Onto 97. Maharaj bowls this one wide outside off, maybe he thought Rohit would come down the track. Sharma though waits for it and then guides it down to the third man fence.

Ohhhh! Rohit had his heart in his mouth for a moment there. KM floats it up on off, it may have stuck in the surface a little. Rohit looks to drive but does so uppishly, it lands just short of short covers.
On middle, kept out nicely.
Rohit comes down the track but does not get to the pitch of the ball. He keeps it out.
Misses out here! This is short and outside off, Sharma plays it late but finds backward point.
On middle, the batter lunges and keeps it out.
Agarwal eases it down to long on and gives the strike to Rohit. The noise level in the stadium goes up as the man on 97 is on strike.
Onto 99 now! This is flatter and on the pads, Rohit works it through mid-wicket and takes two.
Flatter and on off, Rohit keeps it out. 2 balls to go in this over to get to his ton.
Flatter and on off, Sharma goes back and pushes it to covers.

There it is! 100 for Rohit Sharma. 4th in Tests. What a way to grab the opportunity presented. He was struggling to get into the side, here, he gets a chance as an opener and he responds with a ton. Outstanding knock and the whole stadium is on its feet applauding the effort. He gets to the milestone after cutting the ball through point for one. He would now be eyeing a big one, maybe a double ton. He has three in ODIs, can he get his first in Tests here? Also, the bowler has overstepped so it is no ball too.
The last ball is bowled down the leg side, Agarwal lets it be.
Turn, big turn. Maybe because Maharaj slows it up here and lands it on off, it pitches and spins away. Rohit looks to defend but is beaten.
Bowls it slower again but it is fuller. Rohit keeps it out.
On the stumps, it is kept out.
Big turn again! This lands on off again, it pitches and spins a long way away. Rohit's outside edge is beaten by quite some distance.
Shorter and around off, Sharma guides it to point.
The arm ball to end, on middle, Rohit keeps it out. Good batting, he is playing for the original trajectory so the balls which turned aren't playing on his mind.
On the pads, Agarwal pads it away.
Floats it up on off, Agarwal creams it past the cover fielder for two.
Shorter and on the body, Agarwal pulls it through square leg for one.
On middle, kept out.
Floats it up on the leg stump, Rohit defends another ball.
One more ball on middle, Rohit prods forward and keeps it out.
This is eased down to long on for one.
On middle, Rohit lunges forward and keeps it out.
SIX! Rohit is hitting biggies at will here. 5 so far. This time it is the sweep shot. He hits it nicely and it clears the mid-wicket fence.
Shorter and on middle, Sharma pushes it back to the bowler.
Punched off the back foot by the batsman. They pick up a single.
On middle, blocked.
Fuller and on middle, it is driven straight, mid on runs to his left and stops it.
Shorter and on middle, kept out.
This is angled into the batter, Rohit pushes it to mid on.

FOUR! In the air but that flies past the gully fielder. Shorter and outside off, Rohit slashes at it. It flies off the outside edge towards Markram at gully. He fails to react in time and it goes past him down to the third man fence. Maybe he did not spot it that well. Just not South Africa's day.
Shorter and on off, it is pushed to covers.
FOUR! Too easy, just too easy at the moment for Sharma. This is short and around off, Rohit has all the time in the world to go back and push it through covers for a boundary.
FOUR! 200 up. Runs flowing here. This is shorter and outside off, Agarwal waits for it and then guides it past backward point for a boundary.
Flatter and on middle, it is kept out.
Flighted ball on middle, Agarwal defends it.
Loopy ball on off, MA strokes it to covers.
On the pads, it is worked to mid-wicket.

Another half chance! South Africa need to take these if they are to get back in the game. This is tossed up on off, Mayank lunges and tries to keep it out. The ball hits the higher part of the bat and goes low towards silly point. He fails to get down in time.
Shorter and on middle, this is pushed to mid on.
Starts with a good length delivery on middle and leg, Sharma defends it out off the back foot.

FOUR! Poor line from Vernon Philander! Bowls a good length delivery on the pads, Rohit flicks it away nicely towards the fine leg region. Maharaj at deep square leg runs in and tries to make a diving stop to his right but fails to do so. First boundary of the day for Rohit and India are underway on Day 2.
On a length outside off, Rohit drives this to cover for nothing.
BEATEN! Lucky that one for Rohit! It is a good length delivery outside off which kept a little low. Rohit looks to drive but misses it completely. The ball misses the off stump by a whisker.
Outside off, left alone by Sharma.
Starts with a full delivery outside off, Mayank drives it towards the cover region for a single. He gets his first run of the day.
Flighted delivery on off, Rohit defends it off the front foot.
Loopy ball on middle, Sharma defends it back to the bowler.
Flatter delivery around off, Rohit pushes it off his back foot towards the off side.
Floated ball on off, Rohit defends it off the front foot towards the cover region.
Flighted delivery on middle and leg, Rohit defends but it goes off the inside half of the bat towards the leg side.
FOUR! Nicely played from Mayank! Good length delivery outside off, Mayank guides this nicely towards the backward point region for a boundary.
Much better from Philander here! Bowls a good length delivery on middle and leg which kept a little low. Mayank does well to get his bat down in time. The ball rolls towards the leg side.
On a length on middle, Agarwal plays it back to bowler.

Good length delivery on off, Mayank defends it towards cover and calls Rohit for a quick single. Bavuma has a shy at the bowler's end but misses. Agarwal was well in anyway. Mayank moves into the 90s now with that single.
Good length delivery on middle, Rohit defends this off the back foot towards mid off.
Good length delivery outside off, Rohit drives this to cover for a single.
Flighted delivery outside off, Rohit drives this uppishly towards the cover fielder where it goes on the bounce to Bavuma.
Full delivery on middle, Rohit defends this off the front foot.
Floated ball on middle, Rohit defends this off the front foot.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Full delivery on middle, Rohit blocks it out.
Full delivery on middle, Rohit pushes this towards long on and crosses over for a single.
Good length delivery on middle and leg, Sharma flicks it towards mid-wicket for nothing.

FOUR! Beautifully played. Full delivery on the pads, Rohit plays a flick and lofts this over the mid-wicket fielder for a boundary. Rohit plays this shot a lot in ODIs and is continuing in Tests as well.

DROPPED! Rohit survives! Good length ball around off, Sharma looks to defend but gets an outside edge which Quinton fails to hold on to. It deflects off his gloves and rolls towards short third man. Big miss that for the Proteas as that could have been a chance to get back in the game. The batters take a single.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
On a length on middle, Agarwal blocks it back to the bowler.
Good length ball on off, Agarwal defends it off the front foot towards the off side.
FOUR! Delightful! Shortish and outside off by Maharaj, Rohit goes onto the back foot and cuts it towards third man for a boundary.
Another one outside off, this time Sharma pushes it towards extra cover for a single and gets off strike.
Flatter delivery outside off, Agarwal guides it to short third man for a single.
Outside off, left alone by Sharma.
Full delivery on middle, Rohit lunges forward and defends it back to the bowler.
Floated ball on middle, Sharma blocks it out.
Good length ball on off, Agarwal defends it off the front foot towards the off side.
Full delivery around off, Agarwal pushes this towards cover.
Fullish delivery on off, Agarwal pushes this towards the deep point region and crosses over for a single.
Good length delivery on middle, Rohit defends this off the back foot.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Full delivery on middle, Sharma defends but does so uppishly towards mid on. No harm done though.

Run out chance missed! Flighted delivery outside off, Mayank pushes it. The fielder there dives to his left and makes a partial stop. It rolls towards Bavuma at deep cover-point, who initially misfields but quickly redeems himself. Mayank calls Rohit for a second but it is very risky. TB throws it to the bowler's end but misses the direct hit. Rohit dives before the bowler could collect the ball and dislodge the bails but he is well in.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Flighted delivery on off, Mayank drives this towards covers.
On middle, defended it back to bowler.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
FOUR! Beautifully played Flighted delivery outside off, Agarwal guides towards the third man region for a boundary. Mayank just two runs away from reaching his century.
Fuller and outside off, Rohit pushes this straight towards the cover fielder.
Another fuller one outside off, pushed towards cover-point for a single. Agarwal on strike now.
Good length ball on off, Agarwal cuts this one towards point and takes a single. One short of a ton.
Length ball on middle and off, Sharma blocks this one out back to the bowler.
Rohit shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
MISFIELD AND FOUR! On the pads of Rohit, he flicks it towards mid-wicket. The fielder is lazy to get down and lets it through him and the ball reaches the fence. South Africa cannot afford this!

Full delivery on off, Agarwal drives this towards cover where first the short mid off fielder misfields and it rolls towards cover where that fielder also misfields. Mayank wants a single to get to his hundred but is sent back by Rohit.

CENTURY! Maiden Test ton for Agarwal and he is a delighted man! Flighted delivery around off, Mayank gets an educational edge on this. The ball rolls towards the third man region for a single. Excellent innings this from the opener. Since his debut, he has shown that he belongs to this level.
Played to the point region by the batsman for a single.
Flighted delivery on middle, Agarwal defends this off the front foot.
Short delivery on off, Mayank guides this towards cover for a single.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Good length ball on off, pushed towards the man at cover.
on the pads, works this towards the leg side.
Length ball on middle and off, cut to the man at point.
Short of a length ball outside off, guides this one towards backward point as he opens the face of the bat. The batters take one.
Outside off, left alone by Agarwal.
Single off the last ball of the over and Agarwal keeps strike. Length ball outside off, Agarwal guides it through backward point.
Full delivery on off, Agarwal defends this off the front foot.
Flighted ball around off, Agarwal defends this off the front foot towards the off side.
Floated ball on off, Mayank attempts to defend but it goes off the inside half of his bat towards square leg for a single.
Loopy ball outside off, Sharma leaves it alone.
Flighted delivery on middle, Sharma defends this off the back foot.
Flatter delivery around off, Sharma rocks back and punches this off the back foot past the diving cover fielder for a couple.
Short ball outside off, Mayank sways away and lets it go to the keeper.
Good length ball outside off, Agarwal guides this towards the backward point region for a couple.
Short ball aimed at the body, Mayank defends it off the back foot towards the leg side.
Back of a length delivery on off, Agarwal defends this towards the cover region for a single.
Full delivery around off, Rohit drives this beautifully but finds the cover fielder.
Full delivery on middle, Agarwal defends it off the front foot.
Full delivery on middle, Mayank flicks this towards the square leg region and gets back for a couple.
Full delivery on off, Agarwal defends this off the front foot.
Flighted delivery on off, Agarwal defends this off the front foot towards the off side and takes a single.
FOUR! Excellent shot! Comes down the track does Rohit to this flighted ball on middle and lofts this over the bowler's head for a boundary.

FOUR! Back-to-back boundaries for Rohit here! Maharaj bowls a full delivery on middle, Rohit plays a sweep shot which goes off the upper half of his bat and towards the square leg region for another boundary.
Full delivery on the pads, Agarwal pads this one.

Flighted delivery on middle and leg, Mayank comes down the track and drives this towards the long off region for a couple. The fielder at long off makes a diving stop and stops the ball from reaching the boundary.
The batsman has offered no stroke to an incoming delivery.
Flatter delivery on middle, Agarwal defends it off the back foot.
Flat delivery on middle, Mayank flicks it towards the leg side for nothing.
Full delivery on middle, Agarwal plays a sweep shot towards deep square leg and crosses over for a single.

Short delivery on the pads, Mayank rocks back to pull it but gets an inside edge onto the pads and rolls towards the leg side for a single. He would feel that he missed out there as the ball was there to be hit.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Full delivery on middle, Rohit defends this off the front foot.
Flatter delivery on middle, Rohit works it towards the leg side for a single.
Full delivery on the pads, Agarwal pads this one. The ball rolls on to the fine leg fence but it is signaled a dead ball as no shot was offered.
Flighted delivery on the pads, Mayank pads this one.

150 for the Hitman! What a way to grab an opportunity with both hands! This was a shortish ball on the leg side, Sharma pulls this towards square leg for a single. This is the second score of 150+ for Rohit Sharma in Tests.
Down the leg side, Agarwal leaves it alone.
FOUR! Reverse sweep by Agarwal and beautifully executed! Pitched outside leg, Agarwal gets into position and reverse sweeps this one towards the third man boundary.
On the pads, Agarwal works it down the leg side for a single.
Floated on middle and off, pushed back towards the bowler.

FOUR! This time Rohit goes for the reverse sweep and he too gets a boundary. Action replay of Agarwal's shot and the same result as well as the ball crosses the third man fence. Another good over for India as 10 runs came off it.
Floated on the leg pole, pushed towards mid-wicket.

SIX! Smashed over mid-wicket now! The Indian batters becoming aggressive now on every opportunity. Tossed up on the leg pole, Agarwal clears his front foot and heaves it over the mid-wicket fence for a biggie.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.

FOUR! Third reverse sweep in the last two overs! Toying with the South African bowlers now the Indian batters. Pitched outside leg, Agarwal goes for the reverse sweep and plays it very fine towards the third man fence.
On the pads, Agarwal pushes this towards square leg for a single.
On the pads, Sharma glances this towards the man at fine leg.
Floated on off, Agarwal pushes this one towards cover for a single.
Shortish this time, Sharma cuts this one towards point.

FOUR! Bad bowling by Maharaj! On the pads, Sharma gets down on one knee and sweeps this one through to the fine leg region for a boundary. These are freebies to these two batsmen now with no protection in the deep.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Floated on middle and off, Sharma defends it out.
Full and floated on off, Sharma drives this one towards covers.
Full and floated on off, Agarwal pushes this one towards mid off and takes a single.
FOUR! Another freebie to Sharma and he pounces on it! Down the leg side, Sharma just glances it fine on the leg side for a boundary.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.

FOUR! Bad bowling by Piedt and South Africa are bowling themselves out of the game. Another one short and down the leg side, Sharma pulls this behind the fine leg fielder and it races to the fence past the fielder in the circle.
On the pads of Sharma, he flicks it to the man at mid-wicket.
Another one on the pads, Sharma flicks it again towards mid-wicket.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Floated on off, Agarwal prods forward and pushes it back towards mid off.
Floated on middle and off, Agarwal drives this one wristfully towards the man at cover.
Agarwal has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.

300 UP FOR INDIA! What a partnership by Sharma and Agarwal as they have just battered the South African bowling lineup. Flighted delivery on off, Mayank drives this towards mid off and takes a single. These two have just taken the game away from South Africa and it will be very difficult for the visitors to make a comeback. Also, this is the third time that the Indian openers have added 300 runs or more.
Floated on middle and leg, Sharma pushes this towards mid on.
WIDE! On the leg side, but is way wide for the batter to make any contact with that.
On the pads, tucked towards the man at mid-wicket.

FOUR! Reverse sweep and this time towards the cover region. Just outside the leg pole line, Agarwal powerfully reverse sweeps it and the ball races to the boundary at cover. Some pounding by the Indian batters here.
On the pads of Agarwal, he flicks it towards the leg side.

Agarwal has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery. Sharma wanted the run but Agarwal saw Faf du Plessis rushing onto the ball and sends his partner back. Good communication by the batters.
On the pads again, Agarwal tucks this one towards deep mid-wicket and gives the strike to Sharma.
Last ball of the over, defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Full and floated on off, Agarwal pushes this one towards cover for a single.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Sharma prods forward and defends the ball out.

SIX! Sharma charges down the track and tries to loft this one over the cover boundary. He gets it off the outer half of his bat but there is still enough connection on this one to clear Vernon Philander at the long off fence for a maximum. Sharma living dangerously here.

FOUR! Rohit Sharma has taken the risk and lofted it over the covers. This time there is much better connection on it and the ball races to the fence. The ball boys in the deep getting some great fielding practice it seems.

OUT! STUMPED! Finally a wicket for the Proteas and the Hitman has to return to the pavilion. A wonderful innings by him comes to an end with him being dismissed just one short of his best Test score. Maharaj floats this one just outside the off pole line, Rohit looks to prod forward and block it out but the ball spins away and Sharma misses it completely. He loses his balance and his foot is dragged out of the crease as Quinton de Kock dislodges the bails from behind. The square leg umpire raises his finger and Sharma has to walk back. The South African players go up and congratulate him on his great innings as he is dismissed on 176. The massive 317-run partnership comes to an end. It has given very little chance for South Africa to make a comeback into the game.

Flighted delivery on off, Agarwal defends this to point. Pujara wanted a run there but is sent back by Agarwal. Last thing you want is to get run out without facing a ball after sitting out for a long period of time.
Full delivery on off, Agarwal defends this off the front foot.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Flighted delivery on middle, Mayank blocks it out.
Floated ball on off, Agarwal defends this off the front foot.
Loopy ball on off, Agarwal lunges forward and defends this off the front foot towards cover.
FOUR! Floated on middle and off, Pujara just drives this nonchalantly through covers off his first ball for a boundary. Off the mark in style!
Floated outside off, Pujara blocks this one out.
Shortish this time, Pujara cuts it towards the man at point.
Shortish on the leg pole line, Cheteshwar pulls this one towards fine leg and takes a couple as the fielder in the deep mops it up.
Floated on middle and off, Pujara prods forward and blocks it out.
Outside off, Pujara lets this one be and de Kock behind the wickets collects it. 6 off the over.
Full and on the leg pole, Agarwal pushes this one towards mid on.
Full and outside off, Agarwal pushes this one towards extra cover.
Length ball outside off, left alone by Agarwal.
Another good length ball outside off, left alone by the batter.
On the pads, Agarwal tries to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. It rolls behind and is collected by Quinton de Kock.
Length ball outside off, left alone by Agarwal. Not the start that Philander would have wanted after taking the second new ball.
Length ball outside off by Rabada, Pujara does not fiddle with it.
Angling into the batter this time, Pujara does well to block it out.
Length ball outside off, Pujara leaves it alone again.
Good length ball on middle and off, Pujara drives this one straight down the ground. It hits the stumps on the non-striker's end and the ball is stopped.
Outside off, left alone by Pujara.
Good length ball on middle and off, Pujara blocks it out. Back to back maidens for the South Africans.
Fullish and outside off, Agarwal pushes this one towards cover but straight to the man.
Good length ball outside off, Pujara opens the face of the bat and guides this one towards point for a single. First run after 15 balls. A rare sight in this Test match.
Length ball outside off, Pujara initially looks to play at it but pulls out at the last possible moment.
Length ball outside off, Pujara leaves it alone.
On the pads, Pujara tucks this one towards the man at mid-wicket.
BEATEN! Length ball outside off, it pitches and has some movement on it. Pujara tries to fend at it but is beaten.
On the pads of Agarwal, he flicks it towards the man at mid-wicket.

Good length ball outside off, Agarwal looks to defend it but gets a thick outside edge on it. The ball goes towards Faf du Plessis at second slip but falls short of him. It hits him on the shins and that looks like it might have bruised him a bit.
Bouncer on the leg pole line by Rabada, Agarwal does well to duck under it.
Good length ball outside off, Agarwal guides this one towards point.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Good length ball on middle and off, Agarwal blocks it out. And that will be LUNCH ON DAY 2!

OUT! TIMBER! WHAT A START! What a start to the second session by Vernon Philander and the off stump has gone for a spin! Philander pitches this one on the middle and off pole line. It nips away after pitching, beating the outside edge of Pujara's bat and hits the top of off pole as the stump goes cartwheeling. Philander has struck right after the Lunch break and Pujara walks back to the pavilion after scoring just 6 runs. This is the 23rd time that Pujara has been bowled in Test matches. A way back for the Proteas?
Full ball just outside, pushed to cover by Kohli.
Kohli shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
Fullish this time just outside off, Kohli pushes this towards mid off.
Good length ball outside off, pushed towards extra cover.
Length ball just outside off, Kohli pushes this one towards point.
On the pads, Agarwal flicks this one towards the man at mid-wicket.
Fullish ball on middle and off, defended well by Agarwal.
This time on middle and leg, Agarwal pushes this towards mid on.
Good length ball on middle and off, Mayank blocks it out.
Another one on the good length area, Mayank pushes it back to Rabada.
FOUR! One slightly bad ball and Agarwal pounces! Full and wide outside off, Agarwal just leans into the drive and caresses it through covers for a boundary.
FOUR! King Kohli on song now! This one is fuller and just outside the off pole line, Kohli gets on the front foot and creams this one through mid off for his first boundary of the innings.
This time Kohli defends it well by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Length ball just outside off, Kohli blocks it out towards the off side.

On the pads of Kohli, he flicks it towards the man at mid-wicket. He sets off at the start but then gets back into his crease. The fielder has a shy at the stumps and hits. The ball goes towards cover, Kohli tries to sneak in an overthrow but slips midway and has to return.
Defended off the front foot by Virat presenting the full face of the bat.
Good length ball outside off, Kohli pushes it towards point.
Good length ball outside off, Mayank blocks it out towards the off side.
Fullish outside off, pushed towards point.
Length ball angling into the batsman, Agarwal looks to block but it goes off the inner half behind square leg for a single.
Good length ball on middle and off, blocked out by VK.
FOUR! Beautiful shot! Short of a length ball on the leg pole line, Kohli swivels and pulls this through backward square leg for a boundary.
On the pads, Kohli tucks this one towards square leg for a single.
Good length outside off, Agarwal plays it with soft hands and next to himself. Thereafter, stops the ball bouncing around his feet with his bat.
Pushed to the cover region by Agarwal.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Good length outside off, Agarwal commits on the front foot and plays the ball through the covers for a single.
Kohli comes on the front foot and drives it straight to the cover fielder.
An action replay of the previous delivery.
Darted just outside the off pole, Agarwal blocks it out.
Full and floated on off, Agarwal drives this one through the cover region superbly but gets just one.
Tossed up on off, blocked out by Kohli.
Kohli shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
Virat defends this one by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Shortish this one, just outside off. Virat guides this one towards point and takes a single to retain strike.
Played off the front foot towards the covers.
Full on middle and off, plays it off the front foot to point.
Good length ball, outside off. Pushed towards cover-point for a single.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
The batsman has pushed it to the cover region.
Camps on the back foot and pushes the ball to mid-wicket.
Tossed up on middle and leg, pushed towards mid on.
FOUR! Typical Kohli! Full and floated on the middle and off pole, Kohli maneuvers and flicks this one through mid-wicket for a boundary.
This time Kohli pushes this down to long off for a single.
Floated on middle and off, Agarwal defends it.
This one is flighted outside off, Agarwal powerfully drives this towards the cover region for a boundary.
Another one flighted and on off, Agarwal pushes this towards cover and takes a single. Retains strike for the next over.
Good length ball on off. Agarwal defends.
Similar length outside off, tried to play it to the covers but the ball went off the inside edge.

FOUR! 150 UP FOR MAYANK AGARWAL  and he is playing a gem of a knock here! Sprays this one on to the pads and Agarwal gleefully accepts the gift as he flicks it to the fine leg boundary to bring up his 150. Will he score a double ton? That will be the aim in his mind at least!
Pushed to the cover region by the batsman.
Good length outside off, Agarwal plays it towards the off side for a single.
Defends the ball to the cover region.
Floated outside off, pushed towards the cover fielder.
Darted into the off pole, Mayank blocks it out.
BEATEN! Maharaj tosses this one up just outside off. Agarwal looks to go for the drive but misses the ball completely.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.

Floated on the pads, Agarwal looks to paddle sweep this one but misses to get hit on the gloves. The ball rolls towards the off side. The fielding side are asking the question but the umpire shows no interest in it.
Good length ball on middle and off, Agarwal plays it towards point and takes a single.
Back of a length ball, Agarwal defends with a flat bat.
Works it through the covers for a single.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
On a good length outside off, Kohli comes on the front foot and blocks it.
Back of a length ball around off, Kohli comes on the front foot to defend. The ball goes off the inside edge and hit the top of his front pad.
Strays on the pads, worked to mid-wicket. Dot ball.
On middle and off, Mayank defends it out.
FOUR! Maharaj bowls this one down the leg side, Agarwal plays the paddle sweep and the ball races towards the fine leg boundary.
Defended off the front foot by Mayank presenting the full face of the bat.
Short of a length just outside off, Agarwal opens the face of the bat and guides it towards backward point.
Agarwal comes onto the front foot and dabs it onto the ground.
Full on middle and leg, pushed towards mid on.
Full outside off, Kohli defends.
Brilliant piece of fielding! Short around the ribs, Kohli pulls it and the fielder at mid-wicket dives at full length  to save the ball.
On the pads this time, flicked straight to mid-wicket.
Played off the front foot towards point.
Gets in the line of the ball and defends it.
FOUR! Kohli special! Fullish length outside off, VK steps forward and plays a classy cover drive for a boundary.
Full and floated outside off, Agarwal pushes this through the cover region for a couple.
Length ball outside off, helped towards point by Mayank.
Shortish outside off, Mayank plays the square cut for a single.
Full and floated on off, Kohli pushes this one towards mid on for a single.
Another shortish ball, Agarwal pushes this towards deep cover for a single.
Virat has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
FOUR! Tossed up invitingly outside off, Mayank came on the front foot to launch it for a boundary over covers.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Camps on the back foot and plays it to the off side.
SIX! 50 partnership for Agarwal and Kohli! Floated on middle and off, Agarwal clears his front leg and launches this one down the ground, over the bowler's head for a maximum.
Tossed up outside off, MA drives and the cover fielder dives to his right to save the ball.
Plays on the up to mid off.

OUT! CAUGHT AND BOWLED! What happened on that ball? It just hit the deck and paused for a lifetime! Muthusamy gets his first Test scalp and it is the big man, Indian skipper Virat Kohli! Kohli is in disbelief as he sees Muthusamy take the easiest of catches that he will get in his life. Muthusamy bowls this one short and on middle and off, Kohli looks to tuck this one towards the leg side but is early into the shot due to the ball sticking onto the surface. It takes the leading edge of Kohli's bat and goes straight back towards Muthusamy who takes a dolly. He gets the wicket of the Indian skipper and the budding partnership has been broken.
Floated on middle and off, Rahane blocks this one off the front foot.
Rahane shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.

Close call again! Muthusamy bowls this one on middle and leg, it turns away from Rahane after angling in. Rahane gets his bat down just in time as the ball goes off the inner half of his bat towards the leg side.
FOUR! Shortish ball outside off, Rahane plays the square cut and gets off the mark with a boundary. Pressure released!
Defended off the front foot by Rahane presenting the full face of the bat.
Shortish ball outside off, cut to deep point for one.
Tossed up outside off, Rahane goes onto the back foot to poke it through the off side for one.
Tossed up outside off, Agarwal sweeps well towards deep fine leg for three.
Full on middle Rahane drives it to mid on.
Rahane has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
Floated outside off, blocked towards the off side.
Shortish outside off, Agarwal guides it towards backward point.
Mayank defends it from within the crease.
Mayank has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Another one just outside off, Agarwal guides it towards third man.
Agarwal pushes this floated one outside off towards cover for a single.
Floats it outside off, Agarwal plays it back.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Darts it outside off, Agarwal goes on the back foot and cuts it to deep point for one.
Gets in the line of the ball and defends.
Defends it off the front foot.
Overthrow lets to a single! On middle and leg, Rahane flicks it to square leg and denies a single. The fielder fires in a throw at the keeper's end but de Kock fails to collect and concedes a single.
Darted outside off, Rahane cuts it towards deep point for a single.
Full and floated on middle and leg, Agarwal blocks it out.
Full and floated outside off, Agarwal pushes this one towards cover.

FOUR! Agarwal must have had his heart in his mouth for a moment but he has just gone over Bavuma. Full and floated outside off, Agarwal looks to go over the cover fielder but does not get the right elevation.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Mayank has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Drives the ball off the front foot to mid off.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Covers the line of the ball and defends.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Floats it outside off, and it turns in sharply, Rahane goes on the back foot and blocks.
Front foot block yet again.
FOUR! Short of a length ball on middle and leg, it stays a bit low. Agarwal maneuvers as he swivels and pulls this one through square leg for a boundary.
Full and floated outside off, Agarwal tries to cut it but it goes off the inner half onto the pitch.
Tossed up outside off, Agarwal pushes this towards cover.
Another one tossed up outside off, Agarwal drives this through the covers.
Pushed to the cover region by the batsman.
Good length just outside off, Agarwal guides this one towards point for a single.
Tossed on off. Agarwal defends.
SIX! Tossed up on middle and off, Mayank  charges down the track and launches it over the head of the bowler for a maximum. Moves to the 190s.
Tossed up outside off, Agarwal plays it to point.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Works it to cover-point for a single.
Rahane has punched the ball off the back foot.
Agarwal has punched the ball off the back foot. The batters take a single.
Good length ball outside off, cut towards point.
Outside off, left alone by Ajinkya.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Rahane opens the face of the bat and guides it towards third man.
Ajinkya shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
Full and floated outside off, Agarwal kneels and sweeps this one towards the square leg fielder.
Another one just outside off, Agarwal sweeps this one behind square leg for a couple.
Agarwal defends this one by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Agarwal defends this one off the front foot and into the ground.
An awkward shot this one as Agarwal gets down on one knee and pulls this one towards square leg for a single.
Shortish just outside off, Rahane guides this one towards point for a single.
Shortish length ball around off, Rahane taps it towards cover.
Fuller one this time, Rahane looks to work it down the leg side but gets a leading edge towards point.
Shortish ball around off, Rahane goes on the back foot to block.
Slightly full, Rahane comes forward and defends it out with ease
Outside off this time, Rahane plays it gently towards point.
Fuller and on off, Rahane is solid in his defense again. A maiden over this one.
On the middle and leg pole line, Mayank looks to sweep but it goes off the inner half towards short fine leg.
Another one, similar line and length. Mayank looks to sweep but does not get the proper connection.
Pitched on the leg pole line, Agarwal blocks this one out off the back foot.
On the pads of Agarwal, he tucks this one towards square leg and takes a single. Moves on to 198.

Kept low! Tossed up around off, it pitches and stays low. Due to the lack of pace on the surface, Rahane is able to get his bat down in time and defends it out. It goes off the outer half towards third man for a couple.
Last ball of the over, Rahane blocks it out.

200 FOR MAYANK AGARWAL! What an innings this has been by the new man on the block. Full and floated on off, Agarwal comes down the track, pushes it through mid off for a double. A sensational innings this by him and only he knows what his target will be now.
Full and floated outside off, pushed towards cover for one.
On the pads, flicked towards mid-wicket by Rahane.
Another one on the pads, Rahane flicks this one off the pads for a single.
Agarwal shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
Short and wide outside off, Agarwal cuts it towards deep point and the batters take one. Mayank retains strike.
SIX! Another one on middle and off, Agarwal comes down the track and converts this one into a full toss and launches it into the mid-wicket fence for a maximum.
Full on middle and off, Agarwal goes for the sweep but fails to connect as the ball is down the leg side.
On the pads of Agarwal, he flicks this one off his pads for a single.
Rahane blocks this one by getting right behind the line of the delivery.

FOUR! Beautiful shot! Rahane comes down the track, converts this full ball into a full toss and smashes this towards the cover region for a boundary. The boundary brings up the 50-run stand between the two.
Outside off, left alone by Rahane. Another expensive over from Piedt.
Mayank blocks this one onto the ground off the front foot.
Full and floated outside off, Agarwal does well to push it towards the cover region and takes a single.
Another one on middle and off, Rahane defends it out.
Tossed up outside off, Rahane pushes this towards the cover region.
Darted onto the off pole line, Rahane pushes this one towards mid off.

OUT! CAUGHT! Rahane departs now! Brilliant captaincy by Faf du Plessis but Rahane shouldn't be falling for that after being such an experienced batsman. The South African skipper put a silly point to make the batsman think. Maharaj floats this one outside off, inviting the batsman to come down the track and Rahane obliges. He comes down the track and tries to loft this one over the man at cover but he fails to do so and hands a simple catch to Temba Bavuma. Another 50-run stand is broken. Rahane's ordinary form at home continues.
On the pads of Mayank, he flicks it towards square leg for a single.
Shortish and outside off, Jadeja cuts it towards point.
Fuller this time, Jadeja pushes this one towards cover.
Outside off, left alone by Jadeja.
Jadeja plays that off the front foot and into the ground.
Another one on middle and leg, Jadeja blocks it out.
Full and outside off, Mayank looks to dig it out but gets an inside edge on it towards the keeper.
Full and wide outside off, Mayank drives it superbly through the cover region.
FOUR! Full toss outside off, Agarwal accepts the gift and drives this one through the cover region for a boundary.

OUT! CAUGHT! Another magnificent innings comes to an end and this time it is Agarwal who departs. This is another full toss, Mayank looks to drag this one from wide outside off towards mid-wicket. He tries to slog sweep this one wide of mid-wicket but fails to do so. Dane Piedt in the deep runs to his right, a bit forward and takes the catch by going down low. The South African players congratulate him as he walks off the pitch. What a moment for the double centurion as he departs for 215. He takes off his helmet as he walks off the ground and soaks in the applause from the crowd.
Vihari defends his first ball by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Floated outside off, Vihari drives this one towards covers.
Fuller around off, Jadeja pushes it towards long on for a single. He is off the mark with that run.
Flighted ball around off, blocked towards cover by Vihari.
Vihari is underway too. A full ball, he pushes it towards mid off and gets a run.
On middle this time, Jadeja lunges and blocks.
On middle and leg this time, Jadeja pushes it towards long on for a single.
Length ball around off, Vihari gets behind the line of the ball to defend.
Darted onto the boots of Jadeja, he flicks it towards square leg for a single.
Floated on middle and off, Hanuma plays it back to the bowler.
FOUR! Superb shot by Vihari, looks like a shot from a person who is in good touch. Full and tossed up outside off, Vihari drives this one through the cover region for a boundary.

EDGED BUT SAFE! Tossed up outside off, Vihari looks to block this one out but gets a thick outside edge on it as the ball goes past du Plessis past first slip. The ball rolls towards third man for a couple.
On the pads of Vihari, he flicks it away.
Jadeja  has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Outside off, left alone by Jadeja as he pads this one away.
On middle and off, Jadeja blocks this one out off the front foot.
Another one outside off, Jadeja pads it away again.
Darted full and outside off, Jadeja plays this one towards mid on.
Good running between the wickets! Good length ball just outside off, Jadeja opens the face of the bat and guides this one towards third man. They take a quick couple.
Last ball of the over, Jadeja blocks it out back to the bowler.
Vihari comes down the track and pushes this one towards long on for a single.
Short of a length outside off, punched off the back foot by Jadeja.

450 up for India! This one is on the pads, Jadeja tucks this towards square leg and takes a single. The fielder in the deep fumbles, the Indian batters think about the second but opt against it in the end.
Vihari comes down the track and blocks it out.
Vihari comes on the front foot and blocks this one out.
On the pads of Vihari, he flicks it towards the leg side but straight to the man. AND THAT WILL BE TEA ON DAY 2!
Starts with a flighted delivery outside off, Jadeja attempts to defend but gets hit on the pads.
Flat delivery on off, Jadeja flicks it towards the leg side for a single.
Loopy ball around off, Vihari drives it towards covers.
Flatter delivery on middle, Vihari flicks it to long on for a single.
Full delivery on middle, Jadeja flicks this towards mid-wicket for a single.
Floated ball on middle, Vihari defends it out off his front foot.
Good length ball on off, Jadeja pushes it to the point region and takes a single.
Good length delivery on middle and leg, Vihari flicks it towards mid-wicket for nothing.
On a length on middle, Vihari defends this back to the bowler.
Full delivery on middle which kept a little low, Vihari flicks it to square leg for single.
Good length delivery outside off, Jadeja pushes this to the cover region and crosses over for a single.
Full delivery on middle, Vihari pushes it back to the bowler.
Full delivery on off, Jadeja pushes this to long on and takes a single.

NOT OUT! Maharaj bowls a flighted delivery on middle, Vihari comes down the track to defend but misses and gets hit on the pads. The South African players put in an appeal but the umpire is unmoved. Maharaj immediately signals to his captain that he is out and Faf decides to go for the review. The replays roll in and there is no bat involved. Ball Tracker comes in and it is umpire's call on impact. Vihari had come out 3 metres ahead of the stumps and thus, it goes with the umpire's call which was not out. South Africa do not lose the review.
Full and floated outside off, it pitches and turns away as it beats the outside edge of Vihari's bat.

OUT! CAUGHT! Dean Elgar takes the catch at long off and Vihari has to walk back to the pavilion. This one is floated on the off pole line, it pitches and spins away. Vihari looks to go for an inside-out shot over cover but slices it high in the air past mid off. Elgar jogs some steps back and takes an easy catch. Vihari has to walk back after his very short stay at the crease.
Floated on middle and off, Saha blocks it out.
Another one on middle and off, Saha defends it. A successful over for South Africa comes to an end.
Good length delivery outside off, Jadeja guides this to backward point region for a single.
Good length delivery outside off, Saha attempts to cut but misses it completely.
EDGED AND FOUR! Good length delivery outside off, Saha is off the mark with an outside edge, which goes past the slip cordon and into the third man fence.
Good length delivery on off, Saha defends this off the front foot towards the off side.
FOUR! Nicely played from Saha! Good length delivery outside off, Saha guides this towards the third man region for another boundary.
On a length outside off, Saha pushes it to covers off his back foot.
Full delivery outside off, Jadeja drives this to the wide long off region for a couple. The fielder there misfields allowing the batsman an easy two.
Short ball on middle, Jadeja defends this back to the bowler off the back foot.

SIX! Magnificent shot! Jadeja comes down the track to this flighted ball on middle and lofts this handsomely over the deep mid-wicket fence for a huge maximum. That ball has gone deep into the stands.
Flighted delivery around off, Jadeja attempts a reverse sweep but it goes off his pads towards first slip where he makes a diving stop.

4 BYES! Some flight and turn here for Maharaj! Bowls a flighted delivery on middle and leg which spun a little. Jadeja looks to flick but misses. It misses de Kock as well and the ball rolls towards the fine leg fence.
Flatter delivery on middle, Jadeja flicks it towards the leg side for a single. 12 runs have come off the over.
Flat delivery on off, Saha flicks it towards square leg and takes another single.
Flat delivery around off, Jadeja punches this to the deep cover region and takes a single.
Short ball on middle and leg, Saha attempts to pull it but gets hit on the pads. The Proteas appeal but nothing from the umpire. They think of a review but decide against it.
Full delivery outside off, Saha plays a late cut towards the third man region for a couple. Before the ball reaches the ropes, the  fielder makes a sliding stop.
Flighted delivery on the pads, Jadeja looks to flick but misses. It goes on to hit the pads. No appeal this time.
Loopy ball on middle, Jadeja defends this off the front foot.
Flighted delivery on middle and leg, Wriddhiman looks to sweep but misses and gets hit on the pads.
FOUR! Nice shot from Saha! Flighted ball on middle, Saha connects with his sweep this time and plays it towards the deep mid-wicket region for a boundary.
Flighted delivery on off, Saha defends it off the front foot towards the off side.
Flatter delivery around off, Saha punches this to the cover region for a single.
Flatter delivery outside off, Jadeja looks to cut but gets a bottom edge towards first slip who collects it on the bounce.
Short ball outside off, Jadeja cuts it towards backward point for a single.
Flat delivery on middle, Jadeja plays it to cover-point and takes a single.
EDGED AND FOUR! Flighted delivery on middle, Saha looks to flick it to square leg but it goes off the back of his bat and rolls towards the third man fence for a boundary.

OUT! CAUGHT! Saha misses out on this one! It is a rank long hop from Piedt, Saha rocks back and pulls it. He does not time it well. The ball goes straight to Muthusamy at deep mid-wicket. Saha usually does not play this kind of shot but the situation demanded it for him to do so.
Full delivery on middle, Ashwin defends this back to the bowler.
Full delivery outside off, Ashwin blocks it out off his front foot towards the off side.
Flatter delivery on middle, Ashwin flicks it towards mid-wicket.
Short delivery outside off, Jadeja guides it to third man and takes a single.
Full delivery outside off, Ashwin pushes this to cover.
BEATEN! Good ball from Maharaj! Flighted ball outside off spinning away from the batsman, Ashwin looks to defend but fails to put any bat on it due to the spin on it.

Full delivery on middle, Ashwin flicks it to square leg and comes out to take a single. Jadeja obliges but is sent back. The fielder has a shy at the bowler's end but misses. Jadeja was well in though.
Flighted delivery on middle, Ashwin defends this off the front foot.
Another flighted ball on middle, Ravichandran blocks it out.
Flat and on off, the ball keeps low after pitching. Jadeja looks to cut but due to the low bounce he completely misses it.
BEATEN BY A BEAUTY! Full and tossed up on off, it pitches and spins away from Jadeja. He looks to block it but misses the line of the delivery.
On the pads, Jadeja looks to flick but misses and is hit on the pads.
Another one on the pads, Jadeja flicks this one through square leg for a couple.
Jadeja punches this one off the back foot towards point and takes a single.
Full and floated on middle and leg, Ashwin pushes this towards mid on.
Short ball outside off, Jadeja guides this to third man but refuses to take the single.
Short ball outside off, Jadeja rocks back and cuts this towards the point region for a single.
Full delivery around off, Ashwin pushes this to the cover fielder.
Another full delivery on off, Ashwin pushes it to covers again. He has faced 11 balls and is yet to get off the mark.
Short ball outside off keeping a little low, Ashwin looks to cut but fails to put any bat on it.
Loopy ball on off, Ashwin pushes it to the off side for another dot ball. Ashwin looks in no hurry here.
Short ball outside off, Jadeja cuts it towards the cover region for a single and that brings up the 500 for India.
Flighted ball on middle, Ashwin pushes this towards long on for a single. He is finally off the mark on the fourtheenth ball.
Short ball outside off, Jadeja punches this towards the cover region for a single.
Flighted ball on middle, Ashwin comes down the track and defends this back to the bowler.
Flighted ball on middle keeping a little low, Ashwin gets his bat down in time and flicks it to the leg side.
Flatter delivery on middle, Ashwin pushes this to short mid-wicket for nothing. INDIA HAVE DECLARED WITH THE SCORE OF 502/7.
Starts with a good length ball outside off, Elgar defends this out off the front foot.
Good length ball outside off, Elgar leaves it alone.
On a length outside off, Dean lets it go to the keeper.
Back of a length delivery on middle, Elgar defends it off the back foot towards the bowler.
FOUR! Poor ball from Ishant this time! Strays down the leg side, Elgar flicks this nicely towards the backward square leg region for a boundary. South Africa are underway.
Good length ball outside off, Elgar lets it go to the keeper.
Full delivery outside off, Markram lets the ball go to the keeper.
Full delivery on the pads, Aiden flicks it nicely but finds the mid-wicket fielder.
Good length ball on middle and leg, Aiden defends this off the back foot towards the leg side.
Good length ball outside off, Markram shoulders arms to this one.
Good length delivery on off, Markram lunges forward and defends it towards mid off.
On a length on middle, Markram defends it off the back foot. Maiden over to start off from Shami.
Good length ball outside off, Elgar lets it go to the keeper.
BEATEN! Brilliant delivery from Ishant! Bowls a full delivery outside off tempting Elgar to drive but he fails to put any bat on it.
Good length delivery on middle, Dean defends it out towards cover.
Full delivery around off, Elgar pushes this to mid off for nothing.
Good length delivery on middle, Elgar blocks it back to the bowler.

FOUR! Poor bowling from Ishant here! Strays down the leg side again does Sharma. Elgar just helps it on its way towards the fine leg fence for a boundary. Spoiled what was turning out to be a good over.
