Full and flat on middle, Aiden blocks it out.
Another similar delivery, Markram again blocks it out.
Beaten! This time Ashwin pitches this one just outside off, it turns back in sharply. Markram looks to push but it tears him in half as it goes between his bat and pad.
Full and wide outside off, Markram pushes it towards cover for a single. Markram is off the mark with that single.
Elgar punches this one off the back foot.
Last ball of the over, Elgar defends this one off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
FOUR! Bad start by Jadeja! Short and wide outside off, Markram goes onto the back foot and smashes it through point for a boundary.
Markram has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Full and outside off, blocked out by Markram towards the off side.
Shortish this time, Markram blocks this one off the back foot.
Aiden has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Markram looks to defend this one but it goes off the leading edge towards point.
Full and floated on off, Elgar does well to block it out.
On the pads, Elgar flicks it towards square leg for one.
Shortish on middle and off, blocked off the back foot by Aiden.
Markram defends this one off the front foot presenting the full face of the bat.
On the pads of Markram, he flicks it towards square leg but straight to the man.
On middle and off, blocked out onto the pitch.
Darted just outside off, pushed towards mid on.
Similar ball, again pushed towards mid on.
Full and wide on off, pushed towards mid-wicket. Pressure building.
Full on middle and off, pushed towards mid-wicket.

On the pads of Elgar, he flicks it towards square leg. Aiden sets off for a run but Elgar denies it and sets him down the river. Pujara tries to run in and gather the ball but fumbles. He still has a shy at the non-striker's end but Markram has dived in by then and is safe.
On the pads, Elgar works it down the leg side.

OUT! BOWLED! Excellent bowling from Ashwin! Markram's struggle in the subcontinent continues! Flighted ball on off, spinning into the batsman, Markram looks to defend but it goes between the bat and pad and disturbs the stumps. The replay shows that it brushed his front pad on its way. Early wicket for India and they would be looking to make further inroads before the end of day's play.
Full and just outside off, de Bruyn works it towards the leg side.
Beauty by Ashwin! Full and tossed up, de Bruyn looks to come forward and defend it but misses the ball completely as Saha gathers it.

Loud appeal for LBW turned down by the umpire. Ashwin pitches this just outside off, it turns back in. De Bruyn looks to defend but misses to get hit on the back pad. The Indian players put in a loud appeal but the umpire is unmoved. They think that the impact is outside off and thus they do not go for the review. Ball Tracker comes in and shows that they were right.
De Bruyn plays that one off the front foot and into the ground.
FOUR! Outside off, de Bruyn gets down on one knee and reverse sweeps this one through backward point for a boundary. Misses the gully fielder by a whisker who gets out of the way of the delivery.
Full delivery on off, Elgar prods forward and defends this towards the off side.
Flighted delivery on off, Elgar comes down the track and tries to loft it but gets an outside edge past the point fielder for a couple. Lucky for Elgar here. No need to play that shot.
The batsman has driven it through mid-on.
Flighted delivery on middle, Dean flicks it towards mid on.
Full delivery on middle, Elgar defends it out.
Floated ball on middle, Elgar flicks it towards the mid-wicket fielder.
Tossed up just outside off, de Bruyn blocks it out from within the crease.
Another one, shortish, de Bruyn pushes this towards mid on.
De Bruyn plays that one off the front foot and into the ground.
Short and outside off, de Bruyn cuts this one off the back foot but Pujara at point dives to his right and saves at least a couple. Superb fielding.
Ashwin bowls this one on middle and off, de Bruyn defends this one out.
De Bruyn has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Floated just outside off, Elgar pushes this towards mid on.
SIX! What a shot! Counter-attack! Full and floated just outside off, Elgar comes down the track and smashes this one over the bowler's head for a maximum.
Darted just outside off, from round the wicket, Elgar defends this towards the leg side.
On the pads of Elgar, he flicks it towards square leg and takes a single.
Jadeja bowls this one on the middle pole line, de Bruyn pushes it back to Jadeja.
Pitching just outside off and turning away, de Bruyn pushes this one towards point.
Floated just outside off, Elgar manages to keep this one down by defending this off the front foot.
On the pads of Elgar, he flicks it towards square leg.
Elgar blocks this one out nicely off the front foot and into the ground.
Elgar defends this one by presenting the full face of the bat.
Tossed up on middle and off, Elgar has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Tossed up just outside off, Elgar looks push at it but it goes off the outside edge towards short third man.
Length ball outside off to start off, de Bruyn looks to play at it but misses as he does so inside the line of the delivery.
Good length ball on middle and leg, de Bruyn pushes this towards mid on.
Another one fullish around off, pushed towards mid on by de Bruyn.
Good length ball on middle and off, de Bruyn blocks it out back towards Shami.
Good length ball just outside off, de Bruyn blocks it out off the back foot back to the bowler.
Length ball just outside off, Shami gets it to shape back in just a bit. De Bruyn is confident where his stumps are and he makes a good leave.
Darted just outside off, Elgar defends it towards the leg side.
Another one on a similar line, Elgar pushes it towards mid-wicket.
Elgar flicks this one towards the leg side.
On middle and off this time, Elgar flicks it towards mid-wicket and takes a single.
Outside off, left alone by de Bruyn.
Full ball tossed up just outside off, de Bruyn blocks this one out off the front foot.
Floated just outside off, Elgar pushes this one towards cover.
On the pads of Elgar, he looks to tuck it towards the leg side but it goes towards mid off off the leading edge of his bat.
Full and outside off, punched towards cover.
This time a touch shorter, Elgar pushes it towards cover off the back foot.
Dean defends this off the front foot by presenting the full face of the bat.
Outside off, pushed to the man at cover.
On the pads this time, de Bruyn looks to flick this one but misses and is hit on the pad. The Indian players put in muted appeal but nothing from the umpire.
Shortish just outside off, pushed towards cover off the back foot for a couple.
Dean has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Beaten! Floated just outside off, it pitches and turns away. Elgar is beaten all ends up by this delivery.
Down the leg side, Elgar helps it along.
Full and on the pads, driven towards mid on.
De Bruyn shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
Fuller and just outside off, de Bruyn pushes it towards mid off.

OUT! Is that stumped or caught behind? It's the latter. De Bruyn is walking. India are celebrating. Let's find out what happened. Ashwin serves a floated delivery outside off, de Bruyn tries to stride forward and drive it through covers. But the ball spins back in a hint to catch the inside edge. Saha does well to take a sharp catch and then removes the bails off before setting off in celebration. Theunis is not hanging around and immediately starts to walk. South Africa lose their second wicket and are in deep trouble.

Ashwin turns this ball in towards the batter, Piedt looks to block it out but misses and is hit on the pad. The ball lobs up and the fielder at silly point catches it and appeals. There were two sounds but it was of the bat hitting the pad and Piedt survives.
Piedt defends this one onto the ground.
Shortish just around off, Piedt blocks it out off the back foot.
Full delivery on off, Elgar guides this towards the backward point region for a couple.
Flatter delivery on middle, Elgar flicks it towards square leg for a single.

OUT! BOWLED! The nightwatchman does not do his job here as Jadeja removes him easily. Flatter delivery on middle, Piedt looks to defend but is late in bringing his bat down. The ball skids in and goes past him to meet the stumps. Three quick wickets for India.
Flighted delivery on middle, Bavuma defends this off the front foot.

DROPPED! Hanuma Vihari is the culprit! Flatter delivery on middle, Bavuma flicks it but does so uppishly towards short leg. It goes quickly towards him and Hanuma fails to hold on to it. He tries to grab it on the rebound but the ball drops down away from him. It was a tough catch but should have been taken.
Full delivery on off, Bavuma defends it off the front foot towards the off side. A successful over from Jadeja comes to an end.
Darted fuller one on the off pole, Elgar defends it out.
On the pads this time, Elgar flicks this one towards square leg for a single.
Bavuma defends this one off the front foot by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Way outside off, easy leave for the batsman.
On middle and leg, Bavuma blocks this one onto the pitch.
Short and wide outside off, Bavuma cuts this one square and takes a couple as the fielder mops it up in the deep.
Fuller one just outside off, Elgar pushes this towards mid on.

Down the leg side, Elgar looks to glance it but gets it too fine. The leg slip puts in a full stretch dive to his right but still can't reach the ball. The ball rolls towards deep fine leg for a couple.
On the pads of Elgar, he tucks it away towards the leg side.
Tossed up on middle and off, Elgar blocks this one out.
Full and on middle and leg, Dean pushes this one towards mid on.
Floated up on middle and leg, Elgar blocks this one out. THAT WILL BE STUMPS ON DAY 2!
Starts with a good length ball outside off, Bavuma leaves it alone.

EDGED AND FOUR! Lucky start on Day 3 for Bavuma here! Full delivery outside off, Bavuma looks to drive but gets an outside edge which goes through the vacant second slip region and into the third man fence. Ishant is looking at his skipper as if to indicate to put an extra man at slips.
On a length outside off, Bavuma lets it go to the keeper.
Good length ball outside off, Temba shoulders arms to this one.
Full delivery on middle, Bavuma drives this straight back to the bowler.
Back of a length delivery on off, Bavuma defends it off the back foot.
Flatter delivery on middle, Elgar defends it back to the bowler.
BEATEN! Excellent delivery from Ashwin! Flighted delivery outside off, Elgar looks to defend but misses due to the extra bounce and spin on it.
Full delivery around off, Elgar blocks it out.
Floated ball around off, Elgar shoulders arms to this one.
Flighted delivery on middle, Elgar defends it back to the bowler.
Full delivery around off, Elgar drives this but straight to the short cover fielder. Excellent start from Ashwin.
Good length ball on middle, Bavuma blocks it out.
On a length on off, Bavuma defends it to the off side off his back foot.
FOUR! Good shot from Bavuma! Ishant drifts this down the pads of Bavuma who flicks this nicely towards the deep mid-wicket region for a boundary. Ishant has to bowl closer to the middle stump line.
Good length delivery on off, Bavuma rocks on his back foot and blocks it out.
Good length delivery on middle and leg, Bavuma flicks it towards square leg and comes back for a couple.
On a length on off, Temba defends this towards mid off.
Full delivery on middle, Dean defends it back to the bowler.
Flighted ball on off, Elgar blocks it out.
Flatter delivery outside off, Elgar leaves it alone.
Flat delivery on middle, Dean defends it towards silly point.

FOUR! Flighted ball on middle, Elgar lofts this over the mid on fielder for a boundary. Vihari chases after it from mid on and tries to make a sliding stop but is unable to do so. 50 up for the visitors.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Good length ball outside off, Bavuma drives this towards the cover region for a brace.
Good length ball on middle, Bavuma defends it back to the bowler.
Good length ball on middle and leg, Bavuma pushes it to short mid-wicket.
Good length ball on middle, Bavuma flicks it towards the leg side for nothing.
FOUR! Good length delivery on off, Bavuma guides this comfortably past the sliding Rahane at gully for a boundary. Nicely played that.
Full delivery on middle, Bavuma pushes it back to the bowler.
Full delivery on off, Elgar pushes this to mid off.
Flat delivery outside off, Elgar pushes this towards cover.
Full delivery on middle, Elgar defends it off his front foot.
Full delivery on middle, Dean defends it out.
Ashwin bowls with a round arm on middle, Elgar defends it back to the bowler.
FOUR! Good shot from Elgar! Ashwin bowls a flighted delivery on middle, Elgar pushes this towards the long on region for a boundary.

OUT! LBW! Ishant Sharma gets the breakthrough! Good length delivery on off which jags back in, keeping a little low and it hits Bavuma on the back pad. The Indian players appeal and the umpire has no hesitation in giving raising his finger. Bavuma thinks of taking the review but decides against it after having a long chat with his partner, Dean Elgar. Good decision in the end as it looked plumb and the Ball Tracker confirms it as the ball is hitting the middle and leg pole. South Africa lose their first wicket on Day 3.
Good length delivery outside off, du Plessis leaves it alone.
On a length outside off, Faf leaves it alone.
Full delivery on middle, du Plessis flicks it towards the leg side.
Another full delivery on middle and leg, Faf once again flicks it towards the short mid-wicket fielder.
Good length delivery on off, Faf defends it off his front foot.
Flatter delivery on middle and leg, Elgar pushes this to mid on and takes a quick single.
Fullish delivery on the middle stump line, Faf blocks it out.
Floated ball on off, Faf tries to defend but it goes off the outside edge towards point.
Loopy ball on middle, du Plessis blocks it out of his front foot.
Full delivery on middle, Faf pushes it back to the bowler.
Flighted delivery on middle, du Plessis defends it back to the bowler. Just one run from the over.

Good length delivery on middle and leg, Elgar looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pads. There is a stifled appeal for LBW but nothing from the umpire. Replays show that it had taken the inside edge of the bat and then onto the pads.
On a length on middle, Elgar flicks it towards the leg side.
Back of a length delivery outside off, Elgar pushes it towards the point region.
Good length delivery on middle, Elgar defends it towards the leg side.
Full delivery on middle, Elgar plays it back to the bowler.

Full delivery on middle, Elgar attempts to flick but it goes off the inside half of his bat towards one of the short mid-wicket fielders. It goes uppishly but falls just short of the fielder. Maiden over from Shami.
Flighted ball on off, du Plessis attempts to defend but gets an inside edge onto his pads. It rolls towards short leg.
Full delivery on middle, Faf defends this off the front foot.

FOUR! Faf is off the mark with a boundary! Flighted delivery on middle, Faf plays a sweep. There is a fielder at leg slip and another at backward square leg but he gets it to the left of the latter and finds the fence.

FOUR! Back-to-back boundaries for du Plessis! Another sweep. Faf loves the broom, doesn't he? Full outside off again, another flighted ball, du Plessis gets down and sweeps it in front of square leg this time. And he has his wish too. Kohli pushes a man back now.
The batsman flicks it away with a wristy shot.
Flighted delivery on middle, du Plessis defends it out. Good over for South Africa.
Back of a length delivery on off, Elgar defends it to the off side.
On a length on middle, Elgar pushes this one down to mid on off the inner half of his bat.
Fullish delivery on off, Dean drives this towards mid off where Vihari makes a diving stop to his left.

Full delivery on the pads, Elgar tries to flick it but it goes off the inner half of his blade towards backward square leg and takes a single. That is the first run conceded by Shami, on his 22nd ball.
FOUR! Beautiful shot from du Plessis! Full delivery on middle and leg, Faf flicks it nicely towards the deep square leg region for a boundary. He moves on to 12 with three boundaries.
On a length outside off, du Plessis lets it go to the keeper.
Flighted delivery on middle, Elgar defends it out.
Full delivery around off, Elgar defends it off his front foot towards the off side.

Flighted delivery around off which sticks in the surface, it bounces extra off the crack. Elgar tries to defend it but gets a leading edge which lobs towards cover but luckily for Elgar there was no fielder positioned there.
Flighted delivery on middle, Elgar defends it out.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
FOUR! Nicely played! Flighted delivery on middle, Elgar plays a lofted shot over the mid on fielder for a boundary. Surely one of the best patches of play for the visitors in this Test match.
Fullish ball on the off pole line, blocked back to the bowler by du Plessis.
Good length delivery on middle, Faf defends it out.
Fullish delivery on the pads, Faf flicks it towards the fine leg region for a single.
On a length around off, Elgar pushes this towards the off side.
Full delivery outside off, Elgar slices this towards the point fielder.

Another full delivery on middle, Elgar drives but without any timing towards mid off and takes off for a quick single. Vihari comes across and makes a stop but cannot stop the batsman from taking the single.
Flighted ball on middle, Elgar defends it back to the bowler.
Full delivery on off, Elgar drives this towards mid off for a single.
Loopy ball on middle, Faf blocks it out towards short leg.
SIX! Excellent use of the feet from Faf! Tossed up ball on off, Faf comes down the track and lofts it straight down the ground for a maximum.
Flighted delivery on middle, Faf flicks it to mid-wicket. He thinks of a single but it is not there.
Flat delivery on middle, Faf blocks it out.
Flighted delivery on middle, Elgar attempts to defend it but it goes off the inside edge towards backward square leg for a single.
Full delivery on middle, Faf defends it off the front foot.
Loopy ball on middle, Faf pushes it back to the bowler.
Quicker delivery on middle, Faf plays it well towards deep mid-wicket for a single.
Floated ball on middle, Elgar defends it back to the bowler.
Flighted delivery on middle, Elgar lunges forward and defends it out. Good start from Jadeja here.
Flighted on middle and off, pushed towards mid on.
Floated outside off, pushed towards cover by Faf.
Darted onto the off pole line, pushed back towards Ashwin.
Slightly down the leg side this time, Faf flicks it towards square leg.
Full and floated on the pads, pushed down to long on for a single.
Tossed up on middle by Ashwin, Elgar defends it out towards mid off.
Floated on middle and off, it goes towards third man off the outer half of the bat.
Another one just outside off, du Plessis pushes it towards the cover fielder.
Another floated one outside off, pushed towards the cover region again.
On the leg pole line this time, Faf pushes this towards mid-wicket and takes a single.
FOUR! Great execution by Elgar! Floated delivery outside off, Dean gets down on one knee and slog sweeps this one over backward square leg for a boundary.
Tossed up on middle, pushed towards mid-wicket by Dean.
Flighted on the leg pole line, blocked out by du Plessis. It drops just short of short leg which deflects off him towards leg gully.
Similar delivery, Faf again does well to block it out towards the leg side.

FOUR! Swept away! This has happened time and again to Ashwin today and du Plessis is the man who is counter-attacking him. Floated just outside off, du Plessis gets down on one knee and sweeps this towards the square leg fence a boundary. This also brings up the 100 for South Africa.
Du Plessis has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Floated on middle, pushed towards mid on for a single.
Elgar gets behind the line of the delivery and defends it well.
Full and floated just outside off, Faf defends it towards the off side.
Du Plessis stays on the  back foot this time but gets an outside edge on this one in an attempt to defend it. The ball rolls towards the off side.
Faf pushes this towards the cover region and takes a single.
Another one fuller on middle and leg, Elgar pushes it down the ground towards mid on for a single.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.

No ball! Bizzare! Jadeja looks to bowl this delivery but the ball pops out of his hands and goes down the leg side. It reaches the keeper on after four to five bounces on the turf. Faf du Plessis looks to swing his bat but then lets it go with a smile. The umpire signals it as a no ball.
Du Plessis gets right behind the line of the delivery and blocks it out.

FIFTY! 14th Test fifty for Elgar! This has been an excellent innings from Elgar as he has looked at ease. Full delivery on middle, Elgar drives this to long on and takes a single. He knows that his job is only half done and should be looking to continue on to score a big one.
Full delivery on middle, du Plessis pushes this to long on and takes a single.
Another flighted delivery on middle, Elgar drives this through mid on for a single.
The batsman has played it towards mid-wicket. One run added to the total.
FOUR! Beautiful shot from Elgar! Flighted ball on off, Elgar lunges forward and drives this through the cover region for a boundary. 50-run partnership between these two.
Outside off, left alone by Elgar.
Floated on middle and leg, blocked towards the leg side by Faf.
Shortish on middle and leg, du Plessis tucks it towards the leg side.

FOUR! This is pitched outside off, du Plessis looks to defend it but goes off the outside edge towards the third man region. The fielders give it a chase but are unable to keep the ball in play and a boundary is signalled.
Du Plessis opens the face of the bat and guides this one towards third man for a single.
Full and floated on middle and off, pushed towards mid on for a single.
Du Plessis has played that off the front foot and into the ground.

Close one! Elgar shuffles across the wicket and tries to flick the ball towards the leg side. It skids on and Elgar misses the ball completely. Lots of oohs and aahs by the Indian players as Saha collects the ball behind the wickets.
Full and floated on middle and off, Dean pushes this down the ground towards long on for a single.
Faf blocks this one out off the front foot showing the full face of the bat.
Darted on middle and off, du Plessis blocks it out.
Du Plessis blocks this flighted delivery out onto the pitch.
Turn and bounce on that one! Floated just outside off, shortish in length, du Plessis looks to play at it but is beaten. Off the crack maybe?
Floated on middle and leg, Elgar flicks this one towards mid-wicket and takes a single.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
Du Plessis flicks this one off the pad towards the leg side.
Faf flicks this one off his pads towards mid-wicket.
Another one on the pads, du Plessis flicks it away again on the leg side.
Fuller one on the leg side, Faf looks to flick it on the leg side but it goes off the leading edge towards cover for a couple.

SIX! The counter-attack continues. Flighted delivery on off, Elgar plays a slog sweep towards the deep mid-wicket region and the ball lands on the fence on the full. Cheteshwar Pujara from deep square leg runs across to his right but does not reach it. The umpires check whether it is a maximum or a four. Replays roll in and they show that the ball landed on the ropes on the full.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Flighted delivery on middle, Elgar flicks it towards the leg side.
FOUR! Quicker delivery on middle and leg, Elgar flicks it fine towards the fine leg region for a boundary.
The batsman has flicked the ball off his pads.
SIX! Second six of the over for Elgar! Flighted ball on middle, Elgar comes down the track and lofts this over the bowler's head for a huge maximum. 16 runs have come off the over. Excellent batting.
Fullish ball swinging into middle, pushed towards mid on by Faf du Plessis.
FOUR! Fuller and on the pads, Faf just clips it through mid-wicket for a boundary. Great strokeplay by the South African skipper.
Fuller one outside off, pushed towards extra cover.
Good length ball just outside off, du Plessis blocks it out towards the off side.
Full and around off, watchfully blocked out.
That is a snorter! A length ball, outside off, Faf looks to defend but there is extra bounce on that one. Du Plessis looks to fend that out but is beaten in the end.
Flighted ball on off, Elgar defends it off his front foot towards the off side.

DROPPED! Saha is the culprit! Flatter delivery around off, Elgar attempts to defend buts gets a faint edge. It went pretty quickly towards the keeper who does not hold on to it. It hits the pads of Saha and falls just beside him.
Played to mid-wicket region by the batsman.
Flighted delivery on middle, Elgar attempts to sweep but gets hit on the pads. There is an appeal for LBW but nothing from the umpire.
Full delivery on middle, Elgar pushes this to mid on and takes a single.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground. One run added to the total.
Length ball just outside off, pushed towards mid off from the back foot.
Full ball down the leg side, Faf clips it towards fine leg and takes a single.
Length ball just outside off, played towards point by Dean.
Another length ball outside off, Elgar shoulders arms to it.
On the hips of Elgar, he clips it towards mid-wicket.
Nice stop by Rahane! Length ball outside off, Elgar cuts it towards the gully region. Rahane jumps to his left and gathers it with one hand and stops at least a couple of runs for his side.
Darted onto the off pole line, defended off the back foot by Jadeja.
Shortish again on middle, pushed towards mid-wicket.
Jadeja goes fuller this time, Elgar pushes this towards long on for a single.
Just outside off, du Plessis defends it off the front foot.
On the pads of Faf, he flicks it away towards the leg side.
Last ball of the over, pushed towards mid off by du Plessis.
From around the wicket, length ball on middle and off, defended off the back foot by Elgar.
Outside off, left alone by Dean.
Ishant bowls this one on the off pole line, Elgar keeps it out.

Every now and then one delivery is misbehaving off the surface. Good length ball just outside off, it stays low after pitching. Elgar tries to play at it but fails to put any bat on it. Saha also struggles to catch it and it falls in front of him.
Down the leg side, Elgar looks to flick this one but misses. It hits him on the pads and rolls towards mid-wicket.
Length ball just outside off, played towards point by Elgar.

FOUR! Good shot by Faf! Flatter on middle and leg, du Plessis goes into his crease and flicks this one towards square leg. Kuldeep Yadav, the substitute fielder gives it a chase but can't keep it in play as the ball crosses the fence.
Du Plessis plays that one off the back foot and onto the ground.
Flatter just outside off, blocked out by Faf again. Stubborn!
Beaten! Jadeja pitches this one outside off, it spins away from Faf. He looks to defend at it but misses the line of the delivery as it beats the outside edge of his blade.
On the pads, du Plessis flicks it away with a wristy shot towards the leg side.
Last ball of this session, and du Plessis negotiates it nicely as he dabs this one onto the pitch. He starts walking off the field and that will be LUNCH ON DAY 3!
Shami angles it into the pads, Elgar works it down to square leg for a couple.
Good shot! Full outside off, Elgar hits it from the middle of his bat to mid off, where Vihari saves it by diving to his right.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Covers the line of the ball and defends.

Oohh that missed everything. Good length outside off, swings in but not enough to meet Elgar's block or his outside edge. After that it misses the stumps as well and makes its way into the keeper's gloves.
Fullish ball on the pads. Elgar misses the flick, it hits the pads and the ball rolls towards square leg.
Full and outside off, pushed towards mid on.
Around off, a touch short, punched towards mid on again.
Full and outside off, blocked off the inner half towards short mid-wicket.
Outside off, pushed towards cover.
Full and around off, pushed towards point.
Landed outside off, well blocked.
A length ball, around off, Elgar looks to flick but misses and is hit on the pads.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Leg bye! Fullish on the pads, Elgar misses the flick. The ball goes off his pads and rolls to fine leg. They sneak in a leg bye.
First half century for Faf in India! Bowled on the pads, du Plessis flicks it to fine leg for a couple and brings up his fifty.
Jaffa! Angled into the pads. The ball lands on the seam and curves away a bit. Faf flays at it and the ball misses his outside edge.
Takes the ball on the up and plays it to mid on.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
Goes after it again, does Elgar. Full and outside off, Dean lunges and lofts it over mid on but mistimes it. Ishant Sharma runs after it from mid on but cannot get to the ball. Two runs taken.
Around off, watchfully blocked.
The batsman has pushed it to the cover region.
FOUR! This time he connects well. Full and around off, Elgar lofts it over mid on for a boundary!
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Fullish ball outside off, it's pushed to mid on. Hanuma Vihari gets down on his knees but misses. The ball goes off his left knee towards mid off and now the batsmen take a single.
Back of the length, Elgar stays in the crease and blocks it.
Shami continues with the probing line just outside off. Elgar stays on the back foot and defends.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Plays the ball with the angle to mid on.
Full on the pads, it skids through, and takes the toe end of the bat. Hits Elgar flush on the pad. No run taken.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
Nicely tossed up outside off, well defended.
Faster one, outside off, blocked towards short mid-wicket.

FOUR! Fine shot. A bit of a top spinner, outside off, Faf gets down and mows a slog sweep, through mid-wicket. There is Ravindra Jadeja at deep mid-wicket, 15-20 yards inside the circle but the ball is finer, to his right.
Around off, Faf pushes this a bit too hard and the ball goes off the upper half towards mid on. Almost carries!
Full and down the leg side, Faf misses his flick and is hit on the pads.
FOUR! Full ball on middle and leg. Elgar stands tall and flicks it to the mid-wicket boundary. A very confident shot.
No ball! Shami oversteps. Fullish ball on middle and off, Elgar firmly blocked it.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Full ball around off driven to mid off.
On the pads, it's flicked off the pads, to short mid-wicket.
FOUR! Misfield concedes a boundary. Length ball on middle and off, Elgar stays in his crease and punches it towards mid on. Ashwin stationed there dives over the running ball to concede four runs.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Flighted outside off, spinning in, tucked towards short mid-wicket.
Nice flight outside off, worked straight to widish mid on.

OUT! Caught! Finally a wicket falls. It seemed like it would not happen when Faf and Elgar were playing but it has happened. A loose shot from du Plessis and it has brought about his downfall. Full and outside off, Faf gets across and looks to flick but the ball takes the inside edge. Goes straight to Cheteshwar Pujara at leg gully who makes no mistake. 'YES!' screams Virat Kohli on the stump mic as he rushes to celebrate with his number 3. The 115-run stand is broken and South Africa are 125 away from legally making India bat again. Though doubt that Kohli will enforce the follow-on now.
Off the mark straightaway. Works this through mid-wicket for a single.
Around off, defended from the crease.
Full and outside off, Elgar leans and drives it through the covers. Mayank Agarwal chases it from the circle and slides near the fence to stop the boundary. Two runs taken.
Tossed up on middle and off, driven to covers for a couple.
Floated on middle, played back to the bowler.
Goes on the back foot and pokes it back to Jadeja.

FOUR! Good Shot! Flighted full on off, de Kock comes on the front foot and cover drives it spectacularly. The ball defeats the despairing dive by the chasing Ashwin and reaches the hoardings on the boundary.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
The batsman drives the ball straight down the ground.
Darted around off, Elgar brings his bat down at the last moment to block.
Fuller, with more flight, Dean looks to defend and pushes it towards cover.
Fired in on middle and leg, pushed towards the leg side.
Another quicker one outside off, pushed towards cover.

SIX! Fine way to get to a hundred! He is pumped up, isn't he? Full and outside off, Elgar comes down a bit and swings it mightily over mid-wicket! Dean takes his helmet off and then punches the air with his fists.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Goes on the back foot and uppishly cuts the ball through point.
Played to the point region by the batsman.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.

Dropped by Rohit! Tough chance though. Tossed up outside off, and spinning away, de Kock closes the face of his bat too soon. The ball spins away, goes off leading edge and Rohit Sharma at silly point reacts. But it is too quick and the ball brushes his fingers on the right hand and deflects away towards point.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
On the pads comes in with the angle, de Kock misses his flick. It hits him on the pads.
On middle, flicked towards short mid-wicket where Virat Kohli makes a tumbling stop to his left.

SAFE. But what a throw from Ashwin. Full and outside off, Elgar leans and drives it towards cover. Ashwin picks the ball up and has a shy at the bowler's end. Jadeja takes his hand off at the last moment and the ball hits the stumps and the bails fall later. It is referred upstairs and replays show that Elgar is well in.
Full and outside off, watchfully blocked out.
Around off, pushed towards the off side.
Down the leg side, de Kock misses his flick and is hit on the pads.
Full and around off, well blocked out.
Darted in on off, it comes in with the angle and Elgar defends.
FOUR! On the pads, Elgar gets inside the line of the ball and flicks it to the fine leg fence.
The ball has taken the inside edge of the batsman and thudded into his pad.
Comes on the front foot and blocks the ball.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Flighted outside off, Elgar misses the ball due to the spin on it. It hits his pads.
Tossed up on off, de Kock comes on the front foot to defend.
Flighted on a length, it spins in sharply, de Kock plays it with the spin to square leg for one.
Elgar too flicks the ball to the on side for a single. 200 UP FOR SOUTH AFRICA!
Fullish ball outside off, comes in with the spin. De Kock plays it to mid-wicket.
Gets the inner half of the bat as he tries to sweep the ball. It lobs to mid-wicket.
On off, worked to the on side.
Full and outside off, driven straight to cover.
Around middle, tucked straight to mid-wicket for a single.
Tossed up outside off, pushed towards mid off.
Around off, pushed towards cover.
Full and around middle, clipped towards short mid-wicket.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Floats it outside off, worked with the spin to mid-wicket.
Looks to sweep but misses. It hits his pads.
The batsman has played it towards mid-wicket.
On the pads  and it's worked away to the on side.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
Elgar plays that off the front foot and into the ground.
Tossed up outside off, driven straight to cover.
Full and around middle, flicked straight to short mid-wicket.
Nicely flighted outside off, plenty of loop, de Kock gets down and drives but finds cover.
Quicker, around middle, pushed towards short mid-wicket.

FOUR! Not cleanly hit but will still get runs. And four of them. Full and outside off, de Kock looks to go over the top but mistimes it. However, Mayank Agarwal is inside the circle at mid on and the ball clears him. One bounce and into the ropes.
FOUR! Classy hit. Full and outside off, de Kock leans and drives this through the covers. The ball races away.
Jadeja tosses it up outside off, Elgar pokes it to covers. RJ chases it himself. Still concedes a single.

SIX! That is big! Seemed like a top edge but it has cleared the ropes. Full and outside off, de Kock gets down on a knee and aims for the slog sweep. Hanuma Vihari at mid-wicket looks interested for a bit but then just sees the ball sailing over.
FOUR! 19 runs off the last 5 balls! Full and outside off, de Kock looks to defend but the ball goes off his outside edge and and races to the third man fence. Why wasn't there any slip in place?
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
That ball has taken the inside edge of the batsman and thudded into his pads.
Covers the line of the shortish ball and blocks it.
Full and outside off, pushed through the covers for a single.
Full and outside off, eased through the covers for a run.
Eases this through mid on for one.
FOUR! Short and outside off, de Kock cuts it through point for a boundary!
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Landed outside off, played straight to point.
Good length ball, outside off. Elgar drives it to mid off.
Fuller and outside off, Elgar plays it towards point.
Covers the line of the ball and plays it to mid off.
NO BALL! Excess effort from Ishant sees him overstep. The ball goes off the inner half and hits Elgar on the thigh pads. A single taken towards square leg. 50-run stand is up.
Good length ball outside off. De Kock defends it on the back foot.
Fullish ball outside off, de Kock drives it towards cover. That was a good shot but straight to the fielder.
Back of a length ball, cut to the off side. No run.
Full and outside off, pushed towards cover.
Quick single pinched. Elgar pushes this slightly wide of Agarwal at point and sets off for a quick single. De Kock responds nicely.
Outside off, de Kock looks to cut but misses. That stayed low!
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
Short and outside off, cut through cover for a single.
A full toss, around middle, pushed through mid on for a run.
Back of a length ball outside off, Elgar guides it to third man for one. He's batting really well. This positive intent has been there since yesterday.
Ishant slides the ball on to the pads, de Kock flicks it to square leg for a couple.
Beaten! De Kock lazily flays at the ball outside off. He is beaten at the half-baked attempt to play the ball.
It comes back in with the angle now and hits de Kock on the thigh pad.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Length ball, outside off, de Kock guides it to gully.
NO BALL. Oversteps does Vihari, a crime for a spinner. Full and outside off, watchfully defended.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Down the leg side, flick shot missed.
Eases this through mid on for a run.
Full and outside off, pushed straight to cover.
This is on the pads, de Kock goes back and nudges this behind square on the leg side for a run.
Around middle and off, Dean uses his wrists to work it with the angle towards short mid-wicket.
Back of a length ball angling into the pads, de Kock misses the flick and is struck on the knee roll.
On the pads again this time, de Kock flicks it for a single.
On middle and leg worked to the mid-wicket fielder.
Continues with this line on middle and leg, Elgar works it to mid-wicket.
Full outside off, he finally gets a single for his shot through the point region.
On the pads, de Kock gets it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Full toss outside off, driven wide of mid off for a single.
Outside off, pushed towards cover.
Full and around off, pushed towards cover.
Around off, driven back to the bowler.
That stays low. Elgar looks to defend but just about gets his bat down in time. Vihari almost starts to appeal but the umpire signals a no ball for overstepping.
The batsman has driven it straight down the ground.
Outside off, punched towards cover.
Full on leg, it's flicked straight to square leg to Pujara.
On the pads again, it is flicked to the on side for a single. We have been informed that Shubman Gill is on the field. He is on for Ishant Sharma.
Elgar flicks it away with a wristy shot to the leg side.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
On the middle and off line. Elgar, gets behind it and defends solidly.
Full and outside off, driven straight to cover.
Around off, pushed towards the bowler to his left.
Full and outside off, driven straight to cover.
Nice loop outside off, driven straight to cover.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Slow, very slow, plenty of loop, full and around middle, watchfully pushed back.

FOUR! Driven and driven well. Straightish line, Elgar stands tall in his crease and straight drives the ball back past the bowler. Gill on as a sub at mid on chases and makes a valiant effort. It's in vain as the ball wins the race and hits the boundary.
On the pads played to the leg side.
Full on off, played to the covers for a single.
Good length ball on the pads. de Kock misses his flick. Shami appeals but he himself isn't convinced. The umpire was unmoved since it pitched outside leg.
On middle and leg, driven to mid on.
Similar line, is played  towards mid-wicket.
Full and on middle, pushed towards the bowler.
250 UP FOR SOUTH AFRICA! How did this come about? Everyone expected them to fold up inside 150. But they have fought. Full on middle, flicked towards mid-wicket for a single.
Outside off, driven straight to mid off.
On middle and leg, flicked through mid-wicket for a couple.
FOUR! Up and over. Full and outside off, de Kock stays leg side of the ball and lofts it over cover for a boundary!
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
The batsman flicks it away with a wristy shot.
FOUR! Floated outside off, driven through the covers for a boundary. Easy pickings really.
Pushes the ball through the cover region for a single.
Floated outside off played straight to the cover fielder.
Covers the line of the ball and blocks it out.
Full and around off, pushed towards cover.
On middle and off, pushed towards cover again.
Full and outside off, Elgar drives this wide of Ravindra Jadeja at mid off and takes off for a quick single. Had to really hurry in the end.
Tossed up outside off, driven straight to cover.
Landed outside off, de Kock looks to drive but gets a thick inside edge onto his pads.
FOUR! Clean strike! Full and outside off, de Kock leans and drives it through the covers!
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Tossed up on on off, Elgar plays it back to Jadeja.
Floated on middle and off, Elgar tuns it to the on side for a single.
Floated on off, de Kock plays it to cover for a single. HALF CENTURY FOR QdK! His 18th in Tests.
Takes the ball on the up and plays it straight to the mid off fielder.

Beaten all ends up! Credit that to the extra bounce from the new ball. Tosses it up on middle and off, it goes on with the angle and beat the outside edge with the bounce. Saha makes a very good take by jumping up.
Full and around off, pushed towards the bowler.
Outside off, dabbed towards backward point.

FOUR! Just over and dear me, Jadeja collides into the barriers! But he is fine. Full and outside off, de Kock leans and lofts it over cover. Jadeja runs back but cannot get there. Then, he cannot control his speed and crashes into the boards.
Around middle, watchfully defended.
Full and outside off, QdK looks to defend but the ball goes off the outside edge past slip towards third man. Two runs taken.
FOUR! Full and outside off, de Kock drives it through the covers for the second boundary of the over!
Pushed to the cover region by Elgar.
Goes on the back foot and punches the ball to Kohli at mid off.
Floated outside off, Elgar angles his bat and guides it to gully for a single.
FOUR! Tossed up outside off, de Kock waits on the back foot and guides the down to third man for a boundary. Deft touch really.
FOUR! Floated outside off, de Kock comes on the front foot and drives it through coves from the middle of the bat for a boundary.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Down the leg side, helped through square leg for a single.
Around middle and leg, worked through fine leg for a run.
Full and outside off, driven straight back to the bowler.
On middle and off, worked wide of mid-wicket for one.
Full and around off, well defended.
Full again, once more defended by QdK.
Floats it just outside off. Elgar blocks it to silly point.
Leg bye! On middle and off, the ball spin into Elgar, who gets a thigh pad on it. It slides on to fine leg and they run a single.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Covers the line of the ball and defends its on the front foot.
Angled on the leg, it goes off the the pads as de Kock misses his flick.
Around middle and leg, worked through fine leg.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
On middle and leg, tucked through mid-wicket for a single.
Full and around middle, pushed towards the bowler.
Extra bounce! A flighted ball, around middle, de Kock looks to defend but the ball rises sharply and hits him on the glove. He looks shocked, more than surprised.
Full and around off, watchfully defended. TEA ON DAY 3, SOUTH AFRICA TRAIL BY 210!
He blocks this shortish ball out onto the ground towards the off side.
On the pads this time, Elgar flicks this one towards square leg and takes a single.
Again on the pads by Ashwin, this time de Kock flicks this one towards fine leg for a single.
Fullish and outside off, Elgar pushes this back towards Ashwin.
Down the leg side, Elgar blocks this one down.
Floated on the boots, Elgar pushes this towards mid on and takes a single to keep strike.
Good start by Ishant but also a loose shot by Elgar! Length ball just outside off, Elgar goes for the drive towards cover but does so inside the line and misses the ball completely.
Jaffa by Ishant now! Length ball just outside off, the ball pitches and nips away. Elgar looks to defend but it goes past his outside edge in a jiffy.
Attacking the stumps now Ishant, this one keeps a bit low. On middle and off, Elgar brings his bat down in time to block it out.
Another one on the good length, Elgar defends it back towards the bowler.
On the pads now, Elgar tucks this towards the leg side.
Runs on the last ball of the over. On the hips of Elgar, he tucks it towards backward square leg where Pujara mops it up. The batters take a couple.
Full and floated outside off, pushed towards the cover fielder.
Flatter this time outside off, de Kock looks to play at it but bails out eventually.
Darted onto the leg pole line, pushed towards the mid on fielder.
Again on the pads, this time de Kock flicks it towards mid-wicket.

First run off the over as de Kock pushes this one towards mid on for a single. This is now the highest score by a South African wicket keeper in India in Tests. De Kock stepping up at the perfect time!
Full and floated outside off, pushed towards cover by Dean.
Length ball just outside off, de Kock pushes it towards cover-point.
Another length ball on middle and off, de Kock blocks it out.
A rare bouncer in this match, down the leg side. Quinton tries to keep it down as he tries to roll his wrists over it but he is hit on the gloves and the ball falls onto the pitch.
Down the leg side, de Kock tucks it towards mid-wicket and takes a single.

EDGED AND FOUR! Chance but in the vacant first slip region. Don't know why there is a wide first slip in place but not the mandatory one. A good short of a length ball outside off by Ishant, Elgar tries to keep it down but it goes off the shoulder of the bat towards the vacant first slip region. Saha dives to his left but the ball races to the third man fence. The follow-on has also been avoided with this boundary!
Length ball around off, Elgar cuts it towards point and takes a single.

Woah! What happened there? FOUR BYES! Full ball pitched outside off, Elgar looks to play the reverse sweep but it spun and kept really low as the ball went beneath Saha towards the fine leg fence for a boundary.
FOUR! Educated edge this time! Full and floated outside off, Elgar opens the face of his bat but it goes off the outside half of his bat towards the third man fence for another boundary.
Elgar has driven it straight down the ground.
Tossed up around off, Elgar blocks this one out.

FOUR! 150 FOR DEAN ELGAR! What an innings this has been by the southpaw! Gritty, determined, tough! Tossed up just outside off, Elgar opens the face of his bat and guides this one towards third man for a boundary.
Outside off, left alone by Elgar. A good over for the Proteas!
A length ball around middle, angling away, de Kock defends it from his crease.
Full on middle, flicked through mid-wicket for a single.
Outside off, played through point for a run.
Landed outside off, left alone.
The batsman has punched the ball off the back foot.
Full and outside off, driven straight to mid off.
Slower through the air outside off, pushed back towards the bowler.
On the pads this time, Elgar flicks this one towards backward square leg as Vihari dives to his left. The batters take one in the meantime.
Full and floated on middle and leg, de Kock pushes this towards mid on for a single.
Tossed up on middle and off, Elgar looks to defend but it goes off the inside edge and thuds into the pads.
Elgar misses his flick and is hit on the pads.
Another one down the leg side, the batsman has flicked the ball off his pads.
Length ball just outside off, driven towards mid off by de Kock off the back foot.
Short of a length this time on middle, de Kock pulls this one but straight to the man at mid-wicket.
Length ball around off, de Kock pushes this one towards cover-point.
FOUR! Beautiful shot! De Kock stands tall on this length ball, gets on top of the bounce and drives this one towards the long off region for a boundary.
Length ball on middle and leg, de Kock pushes this one towards mid on.
On the pads of de Kock, he flicks this one towards square leg and retains strike by taking a single.
Slower through the air outside off, pushed towards mid off by the batter.
Again tossed up on off, pushed towards mid on this time by de Kock.
De Kock gets right behind the line of the delivery and blocks it out.

DROPPED BY SAHA! Another dropped catch by Saha and this time it is de Kock who survives. Floated one outside off, de Kock looks to defend this one but the ball sneaks from beneath his bat taking the bottom edge. It goes to Saha who cannot react in time to take the catch and it falls just short of Rahane who tries to dive and take it with his right hand. How dearly will India regret this, only time will tell!
The batsman flicks it away with a wristy shot
FOUR! Floated outside off, de Kock drives this one through the cover region gloriously for a boundary.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
Full and outside off, driven straight to mid off.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Around off, pushed back to the bowler.
Outside off, punched through the covers for a single.
Full on middle, de Kock works it towards short mid-wicket, sets off for a single but then sees it is Ravindra Jadeja over there, changes his mind.

Tossed up outside off, it turns back in sharply. The ball takes the inside edge of the bat and goes towards mid-wicket for a single. The short leg fielder was interested for a while but it was too wide for him.

Another chance but de Kock again survives! De Kock looks to defend this one, it takes the inside edge, the ball goes onto the pads and to the left of Saha. He dives to his left but cannot reach to the ball. Fortune favouring the brave?
FOUR! Counter-attack by Quinton! Floated outside off in the rough, de Kock reverse sweeps this one towards third man and it races into the fence.
Floated on middle and off, de Kock pushes this towards mid on and gives the strike to Elgar.
EDGED AND FOUR! Luck on South Africa's side it seems. Floated outside off, Elgar looks to defend but does so inside the line. It goes off the outside edge towards the third man region for a boundary.
Tossed up on off, it has been driven superbly through the covers by Elgar. Two runs added to the total.
Full and around middle and off, driven straight to cover.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Landed outside off, de Kock looks to defend but the ball spins away a mile.
Full and outside off, watchfully blocked.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Around off, watchfully pushed out.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
Huge shout for a catch! Full and outside off, Elgar looks to defend but the ball spins past the outside edge.

OUT! CAUGHT! Finally India get the breakthrough! Brilliant catch by Pujara and the partnership of 164 runs has been broken by Jadeja as he gets his 200th TEST WICKET! This was a floated ball outside off in the rough, Elgar goes for the slog sweep over the mid-wicket fence. He gets just a top edge on it and the ball skies high up in the air. Pujara from mid-wicket runs in hard and dives forward to complete a brilliant catch. Dean Elgar is dismissed after a fantastic knock and India will now look to open up the lower batting order of the visitors. Jadeja is also the second fastest Indian to  reach the 200-wicket landmark. Class!
Flatter on the pads, defended by de Kock on the leg side.
Another one on the pads, works it towards the leg side.
Muthusamy has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery. End of a successful over by Jadeja.
De Kock has defended this one as he gets right behind the line of the delivery.
Floated just outside off, de Kock drives this one towards cover.
FOUR! Short and outside off, de Kock rocks back and cuts it towards the point region. The ball races to the fence for a boundary.
Driven towards the mid off region. One run added to the total.
Muthusamy has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.

DROPPED AND FOUR! Rahane drops one now and this one should have been caught by his standards! Ashwin pitches this one outside off, gives it a lot of air. It pitches and turns away. Muthusamy looks to defend but it goes off the outside edge towards the left of Rahane at first slip. He dives to his left, gets a hand to it but puts it down. It runs down towards the third man region for a boundary. India could have come back strongly had Rahane held onto that one.
On the pads, worked towards the leg side.
Another one on the pads, de Kock works it towards mid-wicket.
On the pads again, de Kock looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads.
Floated outside off, pushed to covers for a single.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Floated on middle and leg, pushed towards mid on by Muthusamy.
Full and outside off, driven towards long off for a single.
Around off, watchfully defended.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Full and well outside off, nicely played out.

Appeal for a catch but it is turned down. No bat at all. Full and outside off, Muthusamy gets across to defend but misses. The ball hits his pads and lobs to second slip. A catch appeal ensues but turned down.
Outside off, a play and a miss.
Darted full and outside off, de Kock pushes this one towards cover and takes a single. Moves to 97 with that.
Flatter and on off, pushed back towards Sir!
Full and outside off, blocked out towards the off side.
Shorter this time, Muthusamy pushes this one towards mid on.
Some turn on that one but still too far away from the stumps. Muthusamy looks to pad this one away but it misses everything and Saha collects it.
Outside off, left alone by Senuran. De Kock on strike now in the next over.

SIX! HUNDRED FOR DE KOCK! What a shot to get to your ton! Flatter this one outside off, de Kock just lofts it over extra cover for a maximum to reach his 5th Test ton! Crucial innings by the T20 skipper of the Proteas!
FOUR! Deft now! A touch wide outside off, this time de Kock goes onto the back foot and guides this one towards third man for a boundary.
Shortish this time, pitching just outside off. It shoots and turns sharply off the surface and beats de Kock.
Quinton has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
De Kock now comes onto the front foot and defends it by presenting the full face of the bat.
On the pads now, he tries to flick but misses and gets hit on the pads.
Full and around middle, worked towards short leg.
Around off, solidly defended.
That spun a mile! Landed outside off, Muthusamy looked to defend but the ball came in a long way and hit his pads.
Full and around middle, watchfully defended.
Around off, nicely blocked.
Full again, nicely kept out.
Length ball just outside off, de Kock gets on the back foot and cuts this one towards backward point. Pujara near the fence slides to his right and the batters take two.
Fuller this time, de Kock pushes this one towards mid off and takes a single.
Good length ball, jagging back in. Muthusamy pushes it towards square leg and takes a single.
Another one which comes back into the southpaw, de Kock pushes it towards mid-wicket.
Goes a touch fuller just outside off, de Kock looks to push this one towards cover but it goes off the inner half towards mid off.
Good length ball by Shami, de Kock blocks it back towards mid off.
Flatter on middle and off, Muthusamy blocks it out.
Floated on off this time, Senuran this time pushes it towards mid off.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Floated full and on off, Muthusamy pushes this one towards cover but it goes off the pads of silly point towards mid on.
Senuran  has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
What a ball! Pitched just outside off, the ball pitches and turns away from Muthusamy. He tries to defend but is completely squared up.
Length ball outside off, de Kock cuts it towards point and the batters take one.
Good length ball just around of, Muthusamy looks to push at it but the ball stays low and beats Senuran's bat.
Outside off, left alone by Muthusamy.
Length ball on middle and off, Muthusamy defends it off the back foot.

NOT OUT! Shami comes steaming in, it jags back in with the angle. Muthusamy tries to defend it but it goes beneath his  bat. He gets hit on the front pad and the Indian players put in a loud appeal. The umpire is unmoved though. Kohli asks Saha whether they should go for the review and after taking some time, they do go for it. Replays roll in, Ultra Edge shows no bat involved. Ball Tracker comes into play and shows it to be missing the leg pole. Good decision making this by the umpire and India lose one of their two reviews.
Length ball jagging back in, almost beats Muthusamy again but this time he gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Full and outside off, de Kock lunges to defend but the ball rips past the outside edge.
Beaten again! Full and outside off, Quinton looks to block again but fails once more.

OUT! BOWLED! Going away, miss. Going away, miss. Coming in, Hit! Beauty from Ashwin. Really set up de Kock nicely. After missing the previous two balls due to the away spin, Quinton comes forward to cover the line on this one. But this does not turn. Goes straight on, is a bit quicker, hence slides through, takes the pad and hits the stumps! Nelson strikes for de Kock and South Africa. Fabulous knock though. The deficit is 132.
Full and outside off, Philander looks to defend but the ball straightens and whizzes past the outside edge.
Around off, defended from the crease.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
Floated just outside off, blocked out by Senuran.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Flatter just outside off, blocked by Muthusamy.
This time Muthusamy pushes it towards mid on and takes a single.
Fuller and tossed up outside off, pushed towards the cover fielder.
Flatter delivery outside off, pushed towards extra cover by Philander.
Pitching just on the leg pole, it goes straight on. Muthusamy misses his defense and is hit on the pads. A stifled appeal but nothing from the umpire.
On the pads, Muthusamy flicks this one properly towards the leg side.

Shortish this time outside off, Muthusamy cuts this one towards point. Ishant from backward point, runs to his left, puts in a slide like a football player trying to stop the ball with his feet but is unable to do so and also injures himself a bit in that attempt. Jadeja runs behind the ball and does the mopping up job as the batters take three.
On the pads of Vernon, he flicks it away with a wristy shot.
Philander defends it back presenting the full face of the bat.
Another one tossed up outside off, Philander blocks it out.
On the pads, Muthusamy works it towards the leg side.

Good bowling by Jadeja. Pitches this one around middle, it zips off the surface and spins away. Muthusamy looks to block but misses the ball completely. It might have hit his pad but the impact was outside off so does not matter.
Senuran has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Fuller and outside off, Muthusamy pushes this one towards long off and takes a couple.
Flatter on off, blocked out by Muthusamy.
Senuran has played that off the front foot and into the ground. End of the over for Jadeja.
Around middle, nudged through square leg for a single.

OUT! BOWLED! 5-fer for Ashwin! Normal services have resumed. India's number 1 off spinner has come back after a long absence in style. This is the 27th time in 66 Tests that Ashwin has taken a 5-fer. Beautifully looped outside off, fuller in length, Philander is enticed and goes for the drive. But the ball spins a long way, takes the inside edge and hits the top of middle and leg sticks. India closing in on batting again but they might want South Africa to bat at least another 2 overs tonight. Else, the hosts might have to bat for a couple of overs.
Straightaway on target to Maharaj, he blocks it out by presenting the full face of the bat.
This time Maharaj goes for the push towards cover but it goes off the shoulder of his blade towards third man. The batters take two.
Maharaj gets on the back foot and defends this shortish ball.
On the leg side, Maharaj flicks this one off his pads towards the leg side.
This one is floated outside off, Muthusamy pushes this one towards cover and takes a single.
Full and floated outside off again, it grips and turns. Maharaj looks to defend at it but misses as he does so inside the line. There was a noise on that one but it was of the bat hitting the pad.
Maharaj defends this one from within the crease.
Beaten again! Maharaj again goes for the drive towards the off side but the ball hurries off the surface and Maharaj misses his shot.
Defended off the front foot by Keshav presenting the full face of the bat. Negotiating out the end of the day here.
Maharaj plays this one off the front foot and onto the ground.
Full and on middle, pushed back to the bowler.
The ball hits the batsman low on the pads. The batsmen have run through for a single. Leg bye signalled by the umpire.

Full on middle, Maharaj works it towards short mid-wicket and calls through for a quick single. 'MUTHU! is the yell. But Muthusamy denies and Maharaj has to scamper back. Shami returns a wide throw to Saha and Maharaj gets back.
FOUR BYES! Full and outside off, Maharaj looks to defend but the ball scoots through, beating the outside edge and the keeper behind. Races to the fence behind.
Landed around off, a play and a miss again.
Outside off, played towards mid-wicket.
Around off, played off the back foot.
Full and outside off, Muthusamy looks to defend but misses and is hit on the pads. India appeal but the umpire indicates bat.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
Around off, solidly blocked out.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
Another awkward forward defense to end the over.
Flatter this time just outside off, Muthusamy pushes this towards cover-point and takes a single.
Muthusamy blocks this one off the front foot towards the off side.
Again just outside off, Muthusamy blocks it back to the bowler.
Muthusamy does well to block this tossed up ball onto the pitch.
Fuller one just outside off, Muthusamy drives this towards mid off and sets off for a single. However, his partner is not interested at all and sends him back.
Last ball of Day 3, Ashwin tosses it up and Muthusamy defends this one off the front foot. South Africa end Day 3 on 385/8.

OHH! What a start from Shami! Back of a length delivery on middle angling into the batsman, Maharaj attempts to defend but the ball cuts him in half and goes through to the keeper. There is an appeal for caught behind but nothing from the umpire. It hits the thigh pad of Maharaj before going to the keeper and Ultra Edge confirms it.
Good length delivery on middle, Maharaj defends it off the back foot towards the bowler.
On a length on middle, Keshav defends it off the back foot.
BEATEN! Good length ball outside off, Maharaj attempts to cut it but misses the ball completely. The ball kept low as it rolls on to the keeper.
BEAUTY! Another excellent delivery from Shami! Bowls it on a length outside off, Maharaj attempts to defend but fails to put any bat on it.
Good length delivery on off, Keshav defends it off the front foot towards the off side. Excellent over from Shami to start off the day.
Flatter delivery down the leg side, Muthusamy looks to flick but misses.
Flighted ball on middle and leg, Muthusamy attempts to defend it but it goes off the inside half of his bat towards the square leg region for a single. First run of the day.
Full delivery on middle, Maharaj blocks it off the front foot back to the bowler.
Flighted ball, down the leg side, Maharaj looks to flick it but does not put any bat on it.

Flighted ball on middle, Maharaj looks to defend but it hits the inside edge and then onto the pads. It rolls towards short fine leg where Jadeja fields it and throws it back to the keeper. Single taken. Hold on! Ultra Edge rolls in and shows that there was no bat involved. Interesting, perhaps an appeal for LBW could have done some good.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
FOUR! Nicely played by Maharaj! Good length ball outside off, Maharaj guides this towards the third man region for a boundary. First boundary of the day for the visitors. The deficit is 111 runs.
Good length ball on off, Keshav defends it off the back foot.
On a length outside off, Maharaj rocks on his back foot and defends it out.
Fullish delivery on middle and leg, Maharaj attempts to defend but it goes off the inside half of his bat towards deep square leg for a single.
Back of a length delivery outside off, Senuran guides it towards backward point for a single.

BEATEN! Good length delivery around off, Maharaj looks to defend but it goes past the bat to the keeper. There is a stifled appeal for caught behind but nothing from the umpire. Another excellent over from Shami.
Flighted ball on off, Senuran defends it off the front foot towards the off side.
BEATEN! Excellent stuff from Ashwin! Flighted ball outside off, Senuran tries to defend it but fails to make contact with it.
BEATEN! Another good delivery from Ashwin! Bowls another flighted one around off, Muthusamy attempts to defend it but does not get bat on it.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Flighted ball around off, Muthusamy pushes it to covers for a single.
Flighted ball on middle, Maharaj defends it towards the leg side.
Good length ball outside off, Muthusamy leaves it alone but the ball passes very close to the off stump. Brave leave that from Senuran.
Good length delivery outside off, Muthusamy attempts to push it but gets an edge towards gully for nothing.
Full delivery on middle, Muthusamy defends it off the front foot.
The batsman lets the ball go outside his off stump.
BOUNCER! Excellent one at that from Shami! It was aimed at the body and Muthusamy does well to duck under it. This should have been bowled more often yesterday but was not seen much.
Good length delivery on off, Muthusamy defends it towards the third man region for a single.
Flatter and just outside off, Muthusamy blcoks it out.
Fuller and floated outside off, Senuran pushes it towards cover and takes a single.
Beauty from Ashwin! Pitching this one just outside off, it is an arm ball that is not picked up by Maharaj. The ball beats the outside edge of his blade by a whisker.

OUT! CAUGHT! Excellent captaincy from Kohli! He put the fielder there right for that shot. Flighted delivery on middle, Maharaj comes down the track and tries to loft it over the long on fielder for a maximum but does not time it well. Mayank Agarwal settles under it at long on and takes a simple catch. Sixth wicket for Ashwin. The deficit is now 106 runs.
Flighted ball on middle and leg, Muthusamy pushes this towards square leg for a single.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Good length delivery on the pads, Senuran looks to flick but it goes off his pads towards the keeper.
Good length ball on off, Muthusamy defends it off the front foot towards the off side.
Full delivery on off, Senuran defends it off the front foot towards mid off.
Back of a length delivery outside off, Muthusamy pushes it towards the cover-point region for a single.
Good length ball outside off, Rabada leaves it alone to the keeper.
FOUR! Full delivery on middle, Rabada flicks it uppishly between the short mid-wicket and mid on fielder for a boundary. 400 up for South Africa. Great fightback this.
Darted just outside off, Senuran blocks it out.
Down the leg side this time, Muthusamy glances this one towards fine leg and takes a single.
Flighted ball on middle, Rabada looks to defend but it hits the pads and rolls onto the pitch.
Flighted ball on middle, Rabada defends it out towards the off side.
Loopy ball on off,Rabada looks to defend but it goes off the edge towards short third man for a single.
Flighted ball around off, Muthusamy pushes it towards cover for a single.
Fullish delivery on middle, Muthusamy defends it off the front foot.
On middle, defended it out.
Flighted ball on middle, Muthusamy looks to paddle sweep it but it goes off the edge and hits the batsman on the neck.

FOUR! Nicely played from Muthusamy! Flighted ball outside off, Muthusamy drives this towards the cover region for a boundary. Pujara runs after it but is unable to stop the ball from going to the fence.
Flighted ball outside off, Muthusamy pads this one. There is a stifled appeal for LBW but nothing from the umpire.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Full delivery on off, Rabada pushes it towards the cover region for a single.
Flighted delivery on middle, Senuran defends it off the front foot.
FOUR! Nicely played! Full delivery outside off, Muthusamy comes down the track and drives this beautifully towards the deep cover region for a boundary.

FOUR BYES! Outside off, left alone by Muthusamy. Saha expected it to spin but it stayed low and went straight on. Rahane at first slip tries to stop it with his right hand but fails to do so and it goes to the third man fence.
Outside off again, left alone by Senuran. This time it is collected by Saha.
Another one a touch short outside off, Senuran looks to cut but is beaten.

NOT OUT! Rabada survives! Flatter delivery on middle and leg, Rabada looks to defend it off the back foot but gets hit on the pads. The Indian players appeal for an LBW but nothing from the umpire. Ashwin convinces Kohli to go for the review. The replays roll in and Ultra Edge shows no bat. The Ball Tracker rolls in and it is umpire's call as it was clipping the top off leg stump. India do not lose the review.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Flighted ball on middle, Rabada defends it off the front foot.
FOUR! Flighted ball around middle, Rabada lofts this beautifully over the mid on region for a boundary. Excellent shot.
FOUR! Back-to-back boundaries for Rabada! Loopy ball on middle, Rabada drives this uppishly towards the long off region for a boundary. The Proteas trail by 76 now.
That ball has taken the inside edge of the batsman and thudded into his pads.
Flatter just outside the off pole, the batter blocks it out.
Darted outside off again, Muthusamy defends it out.
Well outside off, Senuran looks to pad it out but it goes through to Saha.
Similar ball, Muthusamy this time leaves it alone.
A touch inside the line this time, Muthusamy defends it out.
Darted outside off again, Senuran blocks it out. 6 consecutive balls outside off by Jadeja... maybe a plan in place?
BOUNCER! Ishant dishes this one aiming at the body of Rabada who ducks under it.
Good length ball on middle, Rabada flicks it towards the leg side for a single. They think of a single but they see Jadeja running in from deep square leg and they decide against it.
Full delivery on middle, Muthusamy defends it off the front foot back to the bowler.
On a length on middle, Muthusamy defends it out.
Good length delivery on off, Muthusamy blocks it out towards cover.

FOUR! Very well played from Muthusamy! Full delivery on middle, Senuran drives this towards the long on region for a boundary. It goes past the diving Vihari at mid on and into the fence. Crucial runs this for South Africa.
Flatter delivery on off, Rabada defends this off the front foot towards the off side.

OUT! LBW! Good review from India! Saha was against taking the review but Ashwin convinces the skipper to take it and it turns out to be a good one! Flatter delivery on middle and leg, Rabada looks to defend but gets hit on the front pad. Not out says the umpire. India take the review after some thought. The Ultra Edge shows that there was no bat on it. The Ball Tracker rolls in and it is three reds, it is hitting the leg stump. Ashwin gets his seventh. SOUTH AFRICA ARE BOWLED OUT FOR 431.
Starts with a good length delivery down the leg side, Mayank looks to flick but misses it.
Good length delivery on off, Agarwal defends it towards the point region.
Fullish length on off, Mayank defends it off the back foot towards the off side for a single.
On a length on off, Mayank rocks on his back foot and defends it towards mid off.
BEATEN! Good delivery from Philander! Bowls it on a length around off, Mayank attempts to defend it but it beats the bat of Agarwal and goes to the keeper.
Good length delivery on middle, Agarwal defends it out. Good start from Vernon Philander as it is a maiden.
Flatter one to start off by Maharaj, Rohit blocks it out.
Another one pushed flatter outside off, Rohit pushes it out onto the pitch.
Outside off, Rohit defends this one towards the off side.
Sharma has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
FOUR! India and Rohit  are underway in spectacular fashion! Maharaj bowls this one shorter and outside off, Rohit rocks back onto the back foot and pulls this through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Defended off the front foot by Rohit Sharma presenting the full face of the bat.
Beaten! Length ball just outside off, Agarwal looks to play at it but the away movement on this one beats the outside edge of Mayank's bat as he is completely squared up.
This time Mayank gets behind the line of this length delivery and blocks it out.
Length ball outside off, Mayank tries to block it but it goes off the bottom half of his bat past the wickets.
Good length ball outside off, pushed towards cover.
Philander bowling his usual length deliveries, Agarwal stands tall and defends it out.
Good length ball on middle and off, Mayank taps it onto the pitch as the ball rolls towards the cover region.
Floated outside off, Sharma drives this towards cover but the fielder at cover dives low down to his left and does well to stop it.

Misfield! Not what the bowler wants! Back of a length outside off, Sharma cuts this one towards backward point. De Bruyn is lazy to get down and the ball sneaks through him as the batters take a couple.
Outside off, spinning in, left alone by Sharma.
Sharma defends this one by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Another one outside off, turning in but left alone by Rohit.
Sharma defends the last ball of the over onto the turf.
Length delivery around off, Agarwal does well to block it out.
A touch short, near  the hips of Agarwal. He pushes this one towards mid on.
On the pads this time, Agarwal clips this towards mid-wicket.
Good length delivery outside off, Agarwal cuts it well but straight to the man at backward point.
Philander goes fuller now, Agarwal pushes this one towards cover.
Length ball on off, pushed towards mid off. 18 balls in and Agarwal is yet to get off the mark which means three consecutive maidens for Philander as well.
Floated one, full and on the off pole. Rohit drives this one towards long off and takes a single.
Another one tossed up just outside off, Agarwal tries to push at this one but gets a soft inside edge on this one which goes to the first slip fielder on the bounce.
Full and outside off, Agarwal pushes this one towards cover and takes a single.

NOT OUT! It looked close at the start due to the confidence shown by de Kock but Sharma's foot is well in. Good delivery this one by Maharaj. He floats it up, inviting Sharma for the drive. He obliges and takes a step forward but misses the ball. De Kock gathers it and is quick to remove the bails. He is confident that he has got his man. The decision is referred to the third umpire. The replays roll in and shows that the back foot of Rohit is in.
Rohit Sharma has played that off the front foot and into the ground.

SIX! Slog sweeps this one with ease! Floated outside off, Rohit gets down on one knee and just slogs it over the mid-wicket fence for a maximum. No fielder there so a safe shot as well. This is now the most sixes which has been hit in India. 21 sixes so far.
